2832 /// parseArgumentList - parse the argument list for a function type or function
2833 /// prototype.
2834 /// ::= '(' ArgTypeListI ')'
2835 /// ArgTypeListI
2836 /// ::= /*empty*/
2837 /// ::= '...'
2838 /// ::= ArgTypeList ',' '...'
2839 /// ::= ArgType (',' ArgType)*
2840 ///
2841 bool LLParser::parseArgumentList(SmallVectorImpl<ArgInfo> &ArgList,
2842  bool &IsVarArg) {
2843  unsigned CurValID = 0;
2844  IsVarArg = false;
2845  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lparen);
2846  Lex.Lex(); // eat the (.
2847 
2848  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rparen) {
2849  // empty
2850  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::dotdotdot) {
2851  IsVarArg = true;
2852  Lex.Lex();
2853  } else {
2854  LocTy TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2855  Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
2856  AttrBuilder Attrs(M->getContext());
2857  std::string Name;
2858 
2859  if (parseType(ArgTy) || parseOptionalParamAttrs(Attrs))
2860  return true;
2861 
2862  if (ArgTy->isVoidTy())
2863  return error(TypeLoc, "argument can not have void type");
2864 
2865  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVar) {
2866  Name = Lex.getStrVal();
2867  Lex.Lex();
2868  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVarID) {
2869  if (Lex.getUIntVal() != CurValID)
2870  return error(TypeLoc, "argument expected to be numbered '%" +
2871  Twine(CurValID) + "'");
2872  ++CurValID;
2873  Lex.Lex();
2874  }
2875 
2876  if (!FunctionType::isValidArgumentType(ArgTy))
2877  return error(TypeLoc, "invalid type for function argument");
2878 
2879  ArgList.emplace_back(TypeLoc, ArgTy,
2880  AttributeSet::get(ArgTy->getContext(), Attrs),
2881  std::move(Name));
2882 
2883  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
2884  // Handle ... at end of arg list.
2885  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::dotdotdot)) {
2886  IsVarArg = true;
2887  break;
2888  }
2889 
2890  // Otherwise must be an argument type.
2891  TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2892  if (parseType(ArgTy) || parseOptionalParamAttrs(Attrs))
2893  return true;
2894 
2895  if (ArgTy->isVoidTy())
2896  return error(TypeLoc, "argument can not have void type");
2897 
2898  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVar) {
2899  Name = Lex.getStrVal();
2900  Lex.Lex();
2901  } else {
2902  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVarID) {
2903  if (Lex.getUIntVal() != CurValID)
2904  return error(TypeLoc, "argument expected to be numbered '%" +
2905  Twine(CurValID) + "'");
2906  Lex.Lex();
2907  }
2908  ++CurValID;
2909  Name = "";
2910  }
2911 
2912  if (!ArgTy->isFirstClassType())
2913  return error(TypeLoc, "invalid type for function argument");
2914 
2915  ArgList.emplace_back(TypeLoc, ArgTy,
2916  AttributeSet::get(ArgTy->getContext(), Attrs),
2917  std::move(Name));
2918  }
2919  }
2920 
2921  return parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' at end of argument list");
2922 }

2924 /// parseFunctionType
2925 /// ::= Type ArgumentList OptionalAttrs
2926 bool LLParser::parseFunctionType(Type *&Result) {
2927  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lparen);
2928 
2929  if (!FunctionType::isValidReturnType(Result))
2930  return tokError("invalid function return type");
2931 
2932  SmallVector<ArgInfo, 8> ArgList;
2933  bool IsVarArg;
2934  if (parseArgumentList(ArgList, IsVarArg))
2935  return true;
2936 
2937  // Reject names on the arguments lists.
2938  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2939  if (!ArgList[i].Name.empty())
2940  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "argument name invalid in function type");
2941  if (ArgList[i].Attrs.hasAttributes())
2942  return error(ArgList[i].Loc,
2943  "argument attributes invalid in function type");
2944  }
2945 
2946  SmallVector<Type*, 16> ArgListTy;
2947  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i)
2948  ArgListTy.push_back(ArgList[i].Ty);
2949 
2950  Result = FunctionType::get(Result, ArgListTy, IsVarArg);
2951  return false;
2952 }

2954 /// parseAnonStructType - parse an anonymous struct type, which is inlined into
2955 /// other structs.
2956 bool LLParser::parseAnonStructType(Type *&Result, bool Packed) {
2957  SmallVector<Type*, 8> Elts;
2958  if (parseStructBody(Elts))
2959  return true;
2960 
2961  Result = StructType::get(Context, Elts, Packed);
2962  return false;
2963 }

2965 /// parseStructDefinition - parse a struct in a 'type' definition.
2966 bool LLParser::parseStructDefinition(SMLoc TypeLoc, StringRef Name,
2967  std::pair<Type *, LocTy> &Entry,
2968  Type *&ResultTy) {
2969  // If the type was already defined, diagnose the redefinition.
2970  if (Entry.first && !Entry.second.isValid())
2971  return error(TypeLoc, "redefinition of type");
2972 
2973  // If we have opaque, just return without filling in the definition for the
2974  // struct. This counts as a definition as far as the .ll file goes.
2975  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_opaque)) {
2976  // This type is being defined, so clear the location to indicate this.
2977  Entry.second = SMLoc();
2978 
2979  // If this type number has never been uttered, create it.
2980  if (!Entry.first)
2981  Entry.first = StructType::create(Context, Name);
2982  ResultTy = Entry.first;
2983  return false;
2984  }
2985 
2986  // If the type starts with '<', then it is either a packed struct or a vector.
2987  bool isPacked = EatIfPresent(lltok::less);
2988 
2989  // If we don't have a struct, then we have a random type alias, which we
2990  // accept for compatibility with old files. These types are not allowed to be
2991  // forward referenced and not allowed to be recursive.
2992  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::lbrace) {
2993  if (Entry.first)
2994  return error(TypeLoc, "forward references to non-struct type");
2995 
2996  ResultTy = nullptr;
2997  if (isPacked)
2998  return parseArrayVectorType(ResultTy, true);
2999  return parseType(ResultTy);
3000  }
3001 
3002  // This type is being defined, so clear the location to indicate this.
3003  Entry.second = SMLoc();
3004 
3005  // If this type number has never been uttered, create it.
3006  if (!Entry.first)
3007  Entry.first = StructType::create(Context, Name);
3008 
3009  StructType *STy = cast<StructType>(Entry.first);
3010 
3011  SmallVector<Type*, 8> Body;
3012  if (parseStructBody(Body) ||
3013  (isPacked && parseToken(lltok::greater, "expected '>' in packed struct")))
3014  return true;
3015 
3016  STy->setBody(Body, isPacked);
3017  ResultTy = STy;
3018  return false;
3019 }

3021 /// parseStructType: Handles packed and unpacked types. </> parsed elsewhere.
3022 /// StructType
3023 /// ::= '{' '}'
3024 /// ::= '{' Type (',' Type)* '}'
3025 /// ::= '<' '{' '}' '>'
3026 /// ::= '<' '{' Type (',' Type)* '}' '>'
3027 bool LLParser::parseStructBody(SmallVectorImpl<Type *> &Body) {
3028  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lbrace);
3029  Lex.Lex(); // Consume the '{'
3030 
3031  // Handle the empty struct.
3032  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::rbrace))
3033  return false;
3034 
3035  LocTy EltTyLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3036  Type *Ty = nullptr;
3037  if (parseType(Ty))
3038  return true;
3039  Body.push_back(Ty);
3040 
3041  if (!StructType::isValidElementType(Ty))
3042  return error(EltTyLoc, "invalid element type for struct");
3043 
3044  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
3045  EltTyLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3046  if (parseType(Ty))
3047  return true;
3048 
3049  if (!StructType::isValidElementType(Ty))
3050  return error(EltTyLoc, "invalid element type for struct");
3051 
3052  Body.push_back(Ty);
3053  }
3054 
3055  return parseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected '}' at end of struct");
3056 }

3058 /// parseArrayVectorType - parse an array or vector type, assuming the first
3059 /// token has already been consumed.
3060 /// Type
3061 /// ::= '[' APSINTVAL 'x' Types ']'
3062 /// ::= '<' APSINTVAL 'x' Types '>'
3063 /// ::= '<' 'vscale' 'x' APSINTVAL 'x' Types '>'
3064 bool LLParser::parseArrayVectorType(Type *&Result, bool IsVector) {
3065  bool Scalable = false;
3066 
3067  if (IsVector && Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_vscale) {
3068  Lex.Lex(); // consume the 'vscale'
3069  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_x, "expected 'x' after vscale"))
3070  return true;
3071 
3072  Scalable = true;
3073  }
3074 
3075  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt || Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned() ||
3076  Lex.getAPSIntVal().getBitWidth() > 64)
3077  return tokError("expected number in address space");
3078 
3079  LocTy SizeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3080  uint64_t Size = Lex.getAPSIntVal().getZExtValue();
3081  Lex.Lex();
3082 
3083  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_x, "expected 'x' after element count"))
3084  return true;
3085 
3086  LocTy TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3087  Type *EltTy = nullptr;
3088  if (parseType(EltTy))
3089  return true;
3090 
3091  if (parseToken(IsVector ? lltok::greater : lltok::rsquare,
3092  "expected end of sequential type"))
3093  return true;
3094 
3095  if (IsVector) {
3096  if (Size == 0)
3097  return error(SizeLoc, "zero element vector is illegal");
3098  if ((unsigned)Size != Size)
3099  return error(SizeLoc, "size too large for vector");
3100  if (!VectorType::isValidElementType(EltTy))
3101  return error(TypeLoc, "invalid vector element type");
3102  Result = VectorType::get(EltTy, unsigned(Size), Scalable);
3103  } else {
3104  if (!ArrayType::isValidElementType(EltTy))
3105  return error(TypeLoc, "invalid array element type");
3106  Result = ArrayType::get(EltTy, Size);
3107  }
3108  return false;
3109 }

3111 /// parseTargetExtType - handle target extension type syntax
3112 /// TargetExtType
3113 /// ::= 'target' '(' STRINGCONSTANT TargetExtTypeParams TargetExtIntParams ')'
3114 ///
3115 /// TargetExtTypeParams
3116 /// ::= /*empty*/
3117 /// ::= ',' Type TargetExtTypeParams
3118 ///
3119 /// TargetExtIntParams
3120 /// ::= /*empty*/
3121 /// ::= ',' uint32 TargetExtIntParams
3122 bool LLParser::parseTargetExtType(Type *&Result) {
3123  Lex.Lex(); // Eat the 'target' keyword.
3124 
3125  // Get the mandatory type name.
3126  std::string TypeName;
3127  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in target extension type") ||
3128  parseStringConstant(TypeName))
3129  return true;
3130 
3131  // Parse all of the integer and type parameters at the same time; the use of
3132  // SeenInt will allow us to catch cases where type parameters follow integer
3133  // parameters.
3134  SmallVector<Type *> TypeParams;
3135  SmallVector<unsigned> IntParams;
3136  bool SeenInt = false;
3137  while (Lex.getKind() == lltok::comma) {
3138  Lex.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
3139 
3140  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt) {
3141  SeenInt = true;
3142  unsigned IntVal;
3143  if (parseUInt32(IntVal))
3144  return true;
3145  IntParams.push_back(IntVal);
3146  } else if (SeenInt) {
3147  // The only other kind of parameter we support is type parameters, which
3148  // must precede the integer parameters. This is therefore an error.
3149  return tokError("expected uint32 param");
3150  } else {
3151  Type *TypeParam;
3152  if (parseType(TypeParam, /*AllowVoid=*/true))
3153  return true;
3154  TypeParams.push_back(TypeParam);
3155  }
3156  }
3157 
3158  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in target extension type"))
3159  return true;
3160 
3161  Result = TargetExtType::get(Context, TypeName, TypeParams, IntParams);
3162  return false;
3163 }

3169 LLParser::PerFunctionState::PerFunctionState(LLParser &p, Function &f,
3170  int functionNumber)
3171  : P(p), F(f), FunctionNumber(functionNumber) {
3172 
3173  // Insert unnamed arguments into the NumberedVals list.
3174  for (Argument &A : F.args())
3175  if (!A.hasName())
3176  NumberedVals.push_back(&A);

3179 LLParser::PerFunctionState::~PerFunctionState() {
3180  // If there were any forward referenced non-basicblock values, delete them.
3181 
3182  for (const auto &P : ForwardRefVals) {
3183  if (isa<BasicBlock>(P.second.first))
3184  continue;
3185  P.second.first->replaceAllUsesWith(
3186  UndefValue::get(P.second.first->getType()));
3187  P.second.first->deleteValue();
3188  }
3189 
3190  for (const auto &P : ForwardRefValIDs) {
3191  if (isa<BasicBlock>(P.second.first))
3192  continue;
3193  P.second.first->replaceAllUsesWith(
3194  UndefValue::get(P.second.first->getType()));
3195  P.second.first->deleteValue();
3196  }
3197 }
3198 
3199 bool LLParser::PerFunctionState::finishFunction() {
3200  if (!ForwardRefVals.empty())
3201  return P.error(ForwardRefVals.begin()->second.second,
3202  "use of undefined value '%" + ForwardRefVals.begin()->first +
3203  "'");
3204  if (!ForwardRefValIDs.empty())
3205  return P.error(ForwardRefValIDs.begin()->second.second,
3206  "use of undefined value '%" +
3207  Twine(ForwardRefValIDs.begin()->first) + "'");
3208  return false;
3209 }

3211 /// getVal - Get a value with the specified name or ID, creating a
3212 /// forward reference record if needed. This can return null if the value
3213 /// exists but does not have the right type.
3214 Value *LLParser::PerFunctionState::getVal(const std::string &Name, Type *Ty,
3215  LocTy Loc) {
3216  // Look this name up in the normal function symbol table.
3217  Value *Val = F.getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Name);
3218 
3219  // If this is a forward reference for the value, see if we already created a
3220  // forward ref record.
3221  if (!Val) {
3222  auto I = ForwardRefVals.find(Name);
3223  if (I != ForwardRefVals.end())
3224  Val = I->second.first;
3225  }
3226 
3227  // If we have the value in the symbol table or fwd-ref table, return it.
3228  if (Val)
3229  return P.checkValidVariableType(Loc, "%" + Name, Ty, Val);
3230 
3231  // Don't make placeholders with invalid type.
3232  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType()) {
3233  P.error(Loc, "invalid use of a non-first-class type");
3234  return nullptr;
3235  }
3236 
3237  // Otherwise, create a new forward reference for this value and remember it.
3238  Value *FwdVal;
3239  if (Ty->isLabelTy()) {
3240  FwdVal = BasicBlock::Create(F.getContext(), Name, &F);
3241  } else {
3242  FwdVal = new Argument(Ty, Name);
3243  }
3244 
3245  ForwardRefVals[Name] = std::make_pair(FwdVal, Loc);
3246  return FwdVal;
3247 }
3248 
3249 Value *LLParser::PerFunctionState::getVal(unsigned ID, Type *Ty, LocTy Loc) {
3250  // Look this name up in the normal function symbol table.
3251  Value *Val = ID < NumberedVals.size() ? NumberedVals[ID] : nullptr;
3252 
3253  // If this is a forward reference for the value, see if we already created a
3254  // forward ref record.
3255  if (!Val) {
3256  auto I = ForwardRefValIDs.find(ID);
3257  if (I != ForwardRefValIDs.end())
3258  Val = I->second.first;
3259  }
3260 
3261  // If we have the value in the symbol table or fwd-ref table, return it.
3262  if (Val)
3263  return P.checkValidVariableType(Loc, "%" + Twine(ID), Ty, Val);
3264 
3265  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType()) {
3266  P.error(Loc, "invalid use of a non-first-class type");
3267  return nullptr;
3268  }
3269 
3270  // Otherwise, create a new forward reference for this value and remember it.
3271  Value *FwdVal;
3272  if (Ty->isLabelTy()) {
3273  FwdVal = BasicBlock::Create(F.getContext(), "", &F);
3274  } else {
3275  FwdVal = new Argument(Ty);
3276  }
3277 
3278  ForwardRefValIDs[ID] = std::make_pair(FwdVal, Loc);
3279  return FwdVal;
3280 }

3282 /// setInstName - After an instruction is parsed and inserted into its
3283 /// basic block, this installs its name.
3284 bool LLParser::PerFunctionState::setInstName(int NameID,
3285  const std::string &NameStr,
3286  LocTy NameLoc, Instruction *Inst) {
3287  // If this instruction has void type, it cannot have a name or ID specified.
3288  if (Inst->getType()->isVoidTy()) {
3289  if (NameID != -1 || !NameStr.empty())
3290  return P.error(NameLoc, "instructions returning void cannot have a name");
3291  return false;
3292  }
3293 
3294  // If this was a numbered instruction, verify that the instruction is the
3295  // expected value and resolve any forward references.
3296  if (NameStr.empty()) {
3297  // If neither a name nor an ID was specified, just use the next ID.
3298  if (NameID == -1)
3299  NameID = NumberedVals.size();
3300 
3301  if (unsigned(NameID) != NumberedVals.size())
3302  return P.error(NameLoc, "instruction expected to be numbered '%" +
3303  Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
3304 
3305  auto FI = ForwardRefValIDs.find(NameID);
3306  if (FI != ForwardRefValIDs.end()) {
3307  Value *Sentinel = FI->second.first;
3308  if (Sentinel->getType() != Inst->getType())
3309  return P.error(NameLoc, "instruction forward referenced with type '" +
3310  getTypeString(FI->second.first->getType()) +
3311  "'");
3312 
3313  Sentinel->replaceAllUsesWith(Inst);
3314  Sentinel->deleteValue();
3315  ForwardRefValIDs.erase(FI);
3316  }
3317 
3318  NumberedVals.push_back(Inst);
3319  return false;
3320  }
3321 
3322  // Otherwise, the instruction had a name. Resolve forward refs and set it.
3323  auto FI = ForwardRefVals.find(NameStr);
3324  if (FI != ForwardRefVals.end()) {
3325  Value *Sentinel = FI->second.first;
3326  if (Sentinel->getType() != Inst->getType())
3327  return P.error(NameLoc, "instruction forward referenced with type '" +
3328  getTypeString(FI->second.first->getType()) +
3329  "'");
3330 
3331  Sentinel->replaceAllUsesWith(Inst);
3332  Sentinel->deleteValue();
3333  ForwardRefVals.erase(FI);
3334  }
3335 
3336  // Set the name on the instruction.
3337  Inst->setName(NameStr);
3338 
3339  if (Inst->getName() != NameStr)
3340  return P.error(NameLoc, "multiple definition of local value named '" +
3341  NameStr + "'");
3342  return false;
3343 }

3345 /// getBB - Get a basic block with the specified name or ID, creating a
3346 /// forward reference record if needed.
3347 BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::getBB(const std::string &Name,
3348  LocTy Loc) {
3349  return dyn_cast_or_null<BasicBlock>(
3350  getVal(Name, Type::getLabelTy(F.getContext()), Loc));
3351 }

3353 BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::getBB(unsigned ID, LocTy Loc) {

3355  getVal(ID, Type::getLabelTy(F.getContext()), Loc));
3356 }

3358 /// defineBB - Define the specified basic block, which is either named or
3359 /// unnamed. If there is an error, this returns null otherwise it returns
3360 /// the block being defined.
3361 BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::defineBB(const std::string &Name,
3362  int NameID, LocTy Loc) {
3363  BasicBlock *BB;
3364  if (Name.empty()) {
3365  if (NameID != -1 && unsigned(NameID) != NumberedVals.size()) {
3366  P.error(Loc, "label expected to be numbered '" +
3367  Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
3368  return nullptr;
3369  }
3370  BB = getBB(NumberedVals.size(), Loc);
3371  if (!BB) {
3372  P.error(Loc, "unable to create block numbered '" +
3373  Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
3374  return nullptr;
3375  }
3376  } else {
3377  BB = getBB(Name, Loc);
3378  if (!BB) {
3379  P.error(Loc, "unable to create block named '" + Name + "'");
3380  return nullptr;
3381  }
3382  }
3383 
3384  // Move the block to the end of the function. Forward ref'd blocks are
3385  // inserted wherever they happen to be referenced.
3386  F.splice(F.end(), &F, BB->getIterator());
3387 
3388  // Remove the block from forward ref sets.
3389  if (Name.empty()) {
3390  ForwardRefValIDs.erase(NumberedVals.size());
3391  NumberedVals.push_back(BB);
3392  } else {
3393  // BB forward references are already in the function symbol table.
3394  ForwardRefVals.erase(Name);
3395  }
3396 
3397  return BB;
3398 }

3404 /// parseValID - parse an abstract value that doesn't necessarily have a
3405 /// type implied. For example, if we parse "4" we don't know what integer type
3406 /// it has. The value will later be combined with its type and checked for
3407 /// basic correctness. PFS is used to convert function-local operands of
3408 /// metadata (since metadata operands are not just parsed here but also
3409 /// converted to values). PFS can be null when we are not parsing metadata
3410 /// values inside a function.
3411 bool LLParser::parseValID(ValID &ID, PerFunctionState *PFS, Type *ExpectedTy) {
3412  ID.Loc = Lex.getLoc();
3413  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
3414  default:
3415  return tokError("expected value token");
3416  case lltok::GlobalID: // @42
3417  ID.UIntVal = Lex.getUIntVal();
3418  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalID;
3419  break;
3420  case lltok::GlobalVar: // @foo
3421  ID.StrVal = Lex.getStrVal();
3422  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalName;
3423  break;
3424  case lltok::LocalVarID: // %42
3425  ID.UIntVal = Lex.getUIntVal();
3426  ID.Kind = ValID::t_LocalID;
3427  break;
3428  case lltok::LocalVar: // %foo
3429  ID.StrVal = Lex.getStrVal();
3430  ID.Kind = ValID::t_LocalName;
3431  break;
3432  case lltok::APSInt:
3433  ID.APSIntVal = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
3434  ID.Kind = ValID::t_APSInt;
3435  break;
3436  case lltok::APFloat:
3437  ID.APFloatVal = Lex.getAPFloatVal();
3438  ID.Kind = ValID::t_APFloat;
3439  break;
3440  case lltok::kw_true:
3441  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantInt::getTrue(Context);
3442  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3443  break;
3444  case lltok::kw_false:
3445  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantInt::getFalse(Context);
3446  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3447  break;
3448  case lltok::kw_null: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Null; break;
3449  case lltok::kw_undef: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Undef; break;
3450  case lltok::kw_poison: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Poison; break;
3451  case lltok::kw_zeroinitializer: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Zero; break;
3452  case lltok::kw_none: ID.Kind = ValID::t_None; break;
3453 
3454  case lltok::lbrace: {
3455  // ValID ::= '{' ConstVector '}'
3456  Lex.Lex();
3457  SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3458  if (parseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3459  parseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of struct constant"))
3460  return true;
3461 
3462  ID.ConstantStructElts = std::make_unique<Constant *[]>(Elts.size());
3463  ID.UIntVal = Elts.size();
3464  memcpy(ID.ConstantStructElts.get(), Elts.data(),
3465  Elts.size() * sizeof(Elts[0]));
3466  ID.Kind = ValID::t_ConstantStruct;
3467  return false;
3468  }
3469  case lltok::less: {
3470  // ValID ::= '<' ConstVector '>' --> Vector.
3471  // ValID ::= '<' '{' ConstVector '}' '>' --> Packed Struct.
3472  Lex.Lex();
3473  bool isPackedStruct = EatIfPresent(lltok::lbrace);
3474 
3475  SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3476  LocTy FirstEltLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3477  if (parseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3478  (isPackedStruct &&
3479  parseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of packed struct")) ||
3480  parseToken(lltok::greater, "expected end of constant"))
3481  return true;
3482 
3483  if (isPackedStruct) {
3484  ID.ConstantStructElts = std::make_unique<Constant *[]>(Elts.size());
3485  memcpy(ID.ConstantStructElts.get(), Elts.data(),
3486  Elts.size() * sizeof(Elts[0]));
3487  ID.UIntVal = Elts.size();
3488  ID.Kind = ValID::t_PackedConstantStruct;
3489  return false;
3490  }
3491 
3492  if (Elts.empty())
3493  return error(ID.Loc, "constant vector must not be empty");
3494 
3495  if (!Elts[0]->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
3496  !Elts[0]->getType()->isFloatingPointTy() &&
3497  !Elts[0]->getType()->isPointerTy())
3498  return error(
3499  FirstEltLoc,
3500  "vector elements must have integer, pointer or floating point type");
3501 
3502  // Verify that all the vector elements have the same type.
3503  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Elts.size(); i != e; ++i)
3504  if (Elts[i]->getType() != Elts[0]->getType())
3505  return error(FirstEltLoc, "vector element #" + Twine(i) +
3506  " is not of type '" +
3507  getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3508 
3509  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantVector::get(Elts);
3510  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3511  return false;
3512  }
3513  case lltok::lsquare: { // Array Constant
3514  Lex.Lex();
3515  SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3516  LocTy FirstEltLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3517  if (parseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3518  parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected end of array constant"))
3519  return true;
3520 
3521  // Handle empty element.
3522  if (Elts.empty()) {
3523  // Use undef instead of an array because it's inconvenient to determine
3524  // the element type at this point, there being no elements to examine.
3525  ID.Kind = ValID::t_EmptyArray;
3526  return false;
3527  }
3528 
3529  if (!Elts[0]->getType()->isFirstClassType())
3530  return error(FirstEltLoc, "invalid array element type: " +
3531  getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3532 
3533  ArrayType *ATy = ArrayType::get(Elts[0]->getType(), Elts.size());
3534 
3535  // Verify all elements are correct type!
3536  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Elts.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3537  if (Elts[i]->getType() != Elts[0]->getType())
3538  return error(FirstEltLoc, "array element #" + Twine(i) +
3539  " is not of type '" +
3540  getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3541  }
3542 
3543  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantArray::get(ATy, Elts);
3544  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3545  return false;
3546  }
3547  case lltok::kw_c: // c "foo"
3548  Lex.Lex();
3549  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantDataArray::getString(Context, Lex.getStrVal(),
3550  false);
3551  if (parseToken(lltok::StringConstant, "expected string"))
3552  return true;
3553  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3554  return false;
3555 
3556  case lltok::kw_asm: {
3557  // ValID ::= 'asm' SideEffect? AlignStack? IntelDialect? STRINGCONSTANT ','
3558  // STRINGCONSTANT
3559  bool HasSideEffect, AlignStack, AsmDialect, CanThrow;
3560  Lex.Lex();
3561  if (parseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_sideeffect, HasSideEffect) ||
3562  parseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_alignstack, AlignStack) ||
3563  parseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_inteldialect, AsmDialect) ||
3564  parseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_unwind, CanThrow) ||
3565  parseStringConstant(ID.StrVal) ||
3566  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in inline asm expression") ||
3567  parseToken(lltok::StringConstant, "expected constraint string"))
3568  return true;
3569  ID.StrVal2 = Lex.getStrVal();
3570  ID.UIntVal = unsigned(HasSideEffect) | (unsigned(AlignStack) << 1) |
3571  (unsigned(AsmDialect) << 2) | (unsigned(CanThrow) << 3);
3572  ID.Kind = ValID::t_InlineAsm;
3573  return false;
3574  }
3575 
3576  case lltok::kw_blockaddress: {
3577  // ValID ::= 'blockaddress' '(' @foo ',' %bar ')'
3578  Lex.Lex();
3579 
3580  ValID Fn, Label;
3581 
3582  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in block address expression") ||
3583  parseValID(Fn, PFS) ||
3584  parseToken(lltok::comma,
3585  "expected comma in block address expression") ||
3586  parseValID(Label, PFS) ||
3587  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in block address expression"))
3588  return true;
3589 
3590  if (Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalID && Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalName)
3591  return error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in blockaddress");
3592  if (Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalID && Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalName)
3593  return error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block name in blockaddress");
3594 
3595  // Try to find the function (but skip it if it's forward-referenced).
3596  GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
3597  if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID) {
3598  if (Fn.UIntVal < NumberedVals.size())
3599  GV = NumberedVals[Fn.UIntVal];
3600  } else if (!ForwardRefVals.count(Fn.StrVal)) {
3601  GV = M->getNamedValue(Fn.StrVal);
3602  }
3603  Function *F = nullptr;
3604  if (GV) {
3605  // Confirm that it's actually a function with a definition.
3606  if (!isa<Function>(GV))
3607  return error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in blockaddress");
3608  F = cast<Function>(GV);
3609  if (F->isDeclaration())
3610  return error(Fn.Loc, "cannot take blockaddress inside a declaration");
3611  }
3612 
3613  if (!F) {
3614  // Make a global variable as a placeholder for this reference.
3615  GlobalValue *&FwdRef =
3616  ForwardRefBlockAddresses.insert(std::make_pair(
3617  std::move(Fn),
3618  std::map<ValID, GlobalValue *>()))
3619  .first->second.insert(std::make_pair(std::move(Label), nullptr))
3620  .first->second;
3621  if (!FwdRef) {
3622  unsigned FwdDeclAS;
3623  if (ExpectedTy) {
3624  // If we know the type that the blockaddress is being assigned to,
3625  // we can use the address space of that type.
3626  if (!ExpectedTy->isPointerTy())
3627  return error(ID.Loc,
3628  "type of blockaddress must be a pointer and not '" +
3629  getTypeString(ExpectedTy) + "'");
3630  FwdDeclAS = ExpectedTy->getPointerAddressSpace();
3631  } else if (PFS) {
3632  // Otherwise, we default the address space of the current function.
3633  FwdDeclAS = PFS->getFunction().getAddressSpace();
3634  } else {
3635  llvm_unreachable("Unknown address space for blockaddress");
3636  }
3637  FwdRef = new GlobalVariable(
3638  *M, Type::getInt8Ty(Context), false, GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3639  nullptr, "", nullptr, GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal, FwdDeclAS);
3640  }
3641 
3642  ID.ConstantVal = FwdRef;
3643  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3644  return false;
3645  }
3646 
3647  // We found the function; now find the basic block. Don't use PFS, since we
3648  // might be inside a constant expression.
3649  BasicBlock *BB;
3650  if (BlockAddressPFS && F == &BlockAddressPFS->getFunction()) {
3651  if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
3652  BB = BlockAddressPFS->getBB(Label.UIntVal, Label.Loc);
3653  else
3654  BB = BlockAddressPFS->getBB(Label.StrVal, Label.Loc);
3655  if (!BB)
3656  return error(Label.Loc, "referenced value is not a basic block");
3657  } else {
3658  if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
3659  return error(Label.Loc, "cannot take address of numeric label after "
3660  "the function is defined");
3661  BB = dyn_cast_or_null<BasicBlock>(
3662  F->getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Label.StrVal));
3663  if (!BB)
3664  return error(Label.Loc, "referenced value is not a basic block");
3665  }
3666 
3667  ID.ConstantVal = BlockAddress::get(F, BB);
3668  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3669  return false;
3670  }
3671 
3672  case lltok::kw_dso_local_equivalent: {
3673  // ValID ::= 'dso_local_equivalent' @foo
3674  Lex.Lex();
3675 
3676  ValID Fn;
3677 
3678  if (parseValID(Fn, PFS))
3679  return true;
3680 
3681  if (Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalID && Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalName)
3682  return error(Fn.Loc,
3683  "expected global value name in dso_local_equivalent");
3684 
3685  // Try to find the function (but skip it if it's forward-referenced).
3686  GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
3687  if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID) {
3688  if (Fn.UIntVal < NumberedVals.size())
3689  GV = NumberedVals[Fn.UIntVal];
3690  } else if (!ForwardRefVals.count(Fn.StrVal)) {
3691  GV = M->getNamedValue(Fn.StrVal);
3692  }
3693 
3694  if (!GV) {
3695  // Make a placeholder global variable as a placeholder for this reference.
3696  auto &FwdRefMap = (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID)
3697  ? ForwardRefDSOLocalEquivalentIDs
3698  : ForwardRefDSOLocalEquivalentNames;
3699  GlobalValue *&FwdRef = FwdRefMap.try_emplace(Fn, nullptr).first->second;
3700  if (!FwdRef) {
3701  FwdRef = new GlobalVariable(*M, Type::getInt8Ty(Context), false,
3702  GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, nullptr, "",
3703  nullptr, GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal);
3704  }
3705 
3706  ID.ConstantVal = FwdRef;
3707  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3708  return false;
3709  }
3710 
3711  if (!GV->getValueType()->isFunctionTy())
3712  return error(Fn.Loc, "expected a function, alias to function, or ifunc "
3713  "in dso_local_equivalent");
3714 
3715  ID.ConstantVal = DSOLocalEquivalent::get(GV);
3716  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3717  return false;
3718  }
3719 
3720  case lltok::kw_no_cfi: {
3721  // ValID ::= 'no_cfi' @foo
3722  Lex.Lex();
3723 
3724  if (parseValID(ID, PFS))
3725  return true;
3726 
3727  if (ID.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalID && ID.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalName)
3728  return error(ID.Loc, "expected global value name in no_cfi");
3729 
3730  ID.NoCFI = true;
3731  return false;
3732  }
3733 
3734  case lltok::kw_trunc:
3735  case lltok::kw_zext:
3736  case lltok::kw_sext:
3737  case lltok::kw_fptrunc:
3738  case lltok::kw_fpext:
3739  case lltok::kw_bitcast:
3740  case lltok::kw_addrspacecast:
3741  case lltok::kw_uitofp:
3742  case lltok::kw_sitofp:
3743  case lltok::kw_fptoui:
3744  case lltok::kw_fptosi:
3745  case lltok::kw_inttoptr:
3746  case lltok::kw_ptrtoint: {
3747  unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3748  Type *DestTy = nullptr;
3749  Constant *SrcVal;
3750  Lex.Lex();
3751  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' after constantexpr cast") ||
3752  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(SrcVal) ||
3753  parseToken(lltok::kw_to, "expected 'to' in constantexpr cast") ||
3754  parseType(DestTy) ||
3755  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' at end of constantexpr cast"))
3756  return true;
3757  if (!CastInst::castIsValid((Instruction::CastOps)Opc, SrcVal, DestTy))
3758  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid cast opcode for cast from '" +
3759  getTypeString(SrcVal->getType()) + "' to '" +
3760  getTypeString(DestTy) + "'");
3761  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getCast((Instruction::CastOps)Opc,
3762  SrcVal, DestTy);
3763  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3764  return false;
3765  }
3766  case lltok::kw_extractvalue:
3767  return error(ID.Loc, "extractvalue constexprs are no longer supported");
3768  case lltok::kw_insertvalue:
3769  return error(ID.Loc, "insertvalue constexprs are no longer supported");
3770  case lltok::kw_udiv:
3771  return error(ID.Loc, "udiv constexprs are no longer supported");
3772  case lltok::kw_sdiv:
3773  return error(ID.Loc, "sdiv constexprs are no longer supported");
3774  case lltok::kw_urem:
3775  return error(ID.Loc, "urem constexprs are no longer supported");
3776  case lltok::kw_srem:
3777  return error(ID.Loc, "srem constexprs are no longer supported");
3778  case lltok::kw_fadd:
3779  return error(ID.Loc, "fadd constexprs are no longer supported");
3780  case lltok::kw_fsub:
3781  return error(ID.Loc, "fsub constexprs are no longer supported");
3782  case lltok::kw_fmul:
3783  return error(ID.Loc, "fmul constexprs are no longer supported");
3784  case lltok::kw_fdiv:
3785  return error(ID.Loc, "fdiv constexprs are no longer supported");
3786  case lltok::kw_frem:
3787  return error(ID.Loc, "frem constexprs are no longer supported");
3788  case lltok::kw_fneg:
3789  return error(ID.Loc, "fneg constexprs are no longer supported");
3790  case lltok::kw_icmp:
3791  case lltok::kw_fcmp: {
3792  unsigned PredVal, Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3793  Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3794  Lex.Lex();
3795  if (parseCmpPredicate(PredVal, Opc) ||
3796  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in compare constantexpr") ||
3797  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3798  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in compare constantexpr") ||
3799  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3800  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in compare constantexpr"))
3801  return true;
3802 
3803  if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3804  return error(ID.Loc, "compare operands must have the same type");
3805 
3806  CmpInst::Predicate Pred = (CmpInst::Predicate)PredVal;
3807 
3808  if (Opc == Instruction::FCmp) {
3809  if (!Val0->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3810  return error(ID.Loc, "fcmp requires floating point operands");
3811  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getFCmp(Pred, Val0, Val1);
3812  } else {
3813  assert(Opc == Instruction::ICmp && "Unexpected opcode for CmpInst!");
3814  if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() &&
3815  !Val0->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
3816  return error(ID.Loc, "icmp requires pointer or integer operands");
3817  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred, Val0, Val1);
3818  }
3819  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3820  return false;
3821  }
3822 
3823  // Binary Operators.
3824  case lltok::kw_add:
3825  case lltok::kw_sub:
3826  case lltok::kw_mul:
3827  case lltok::kw_shl:
3828  case lltok::kw_lshr:
3829  case lltok::kw_ashr: {
3830  bool NUW = false;
3831  bool NSW = false;
3832  bool Exact = false;
3833  unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3834  Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3835  Lex.Lex();
3836  if (Opc == Instruction::Add || Opc == Instruction::Sub ||
3837  Opc == Instruction::Mul || Opc == Instruction::Shl) {
3838  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw))
3839  NUW = true;
3840  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nsw)) {
3841  NSW = true;
3842  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw))
3843  NUW = true;
3844  }
3845  } else if (Opc == Instruction::SDiv || Opc == Instruction::UDiv ||
3846  Opc == Instruction::LShr || Opc == Instruction::AShr) {
3847  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_exact))
3848  Exact = true;
3849  }
3850  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in binary constantexpr") ||
3851  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3852  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in binary constantexpr") ||
3853  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3854  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in binary constantexpr"))
3855  return true;
3856  if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3857  return error(ID.Loc, "operands of constexpr must have same type");
3858  // Check that the type is valid for the operator.
3859  switch (Opc) {
3860  case Instruction::Add:
3861  case Instruction::Sub:
3862  case Instruction::Mul:
3863  case Instruction::UDiv:
3864  case Instruction::SDiv:
3865  case Instruction::URem:
3866  case Instruction::SRem:
3867  case Instruction::Shl:
3868  case Instruction::AShr:
3869  case Instruction::LShr:
3870  if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3871  return error(ID.Loc, "constexpr requires integer operands");
3872  break;
3873  case Instruction::FAdd:
3874  case Instruction::FSub:
3875  case Instruction::FMul:
3876  case Instruction::FDiv:
3877  case Instruction::FRem:
3878  if (!Val0->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3879  return error(ID.Loc, "constexpr requires fp operands");
3880  break;
3881  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown binary operator!");
3882  }
3883  unsigned Flags = 0;
3884  if (NUW) Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap;
3885  if (NSW) Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap;
3886  if (Exact) Flags |= PossiblyExactOperator::IsExact;
3887  Constant *C = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, Val0, Val1, Flags);
3888  ID.ConstantVal = C;
3889  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3890  return false;
3891  }
3892 
3893  // Logical Operations
3894  case lltok::kw_and:
3895  case lltok::kw_or:
3896  case lltok::kw_xor: {
3897  unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3898  Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3899  Lex.Lex();
3900  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in logical constantexpr") ||
3901  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3902  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in logical constantexpr") ||
3903  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3904  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in logical constantexpr"))
3905  return true;
3906  if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3907  return error(ID.Loc, "operands of constexpr must have same type");
3908  if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3909  return error(ID.Loc,
3910  "constexpr requires integer or integer vector operands");
3911  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, Val0, Val1);
3912  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3913  return false;
3914  }
3915 
3916  case lltok::kw_getelementptr:
3917  case lltok::kw_shufflevector:
3918  case lltok::kw_insertelement:
3919  case lltok::kw_extractelement:
3920  case lltok::kw_select: {
3921  unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3922  SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3923  bool InBounds = false;
3924  Type *Ty;
3925  Lex.Lex();
3926 
3927  if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr)
3928  InBounds = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inbounds);
3929 
3930  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in constantexpr"))
3931  return true;
3932 
3933  LocTy ExplicitTypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3934  if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr) {
3935  if (parseType(Ty) ||
3936  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma after getelementptr's type"))
3937  return true;
3938  }
3939 
3940  std::optional<unsigned> InRangeOp;
3941  if (parseGlobalValueVector(
3942  Elts, Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr ? &InRangeOp : nullptr) ||
3943  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in constantexpr"))
3944  return true;
3945 
3946  if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr) {
3947  if (Elts.size() == 0 ||
3948  !Elts[0]->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
3949  return error(ID.Loc, "base of getelementptr must be a pointer");
3950 
3951  Type *BaseType = Elts[0]->getType();
3952  auto *BasePointerType = cast<PointerType>(BaseType->getScalarType());
3953  if (!BasePointerType->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Ty)) {
3954  return error(
3955  ExplicitTypeLoc,
3956  typeComparisonErrorMessage(
3957  "explicit pointee type doesn't match operand's pointee type",
3958  Ty, BasePointerType->getNonOpaquePointerElementType()));
3959  }
3960 
3961  unsigned GEPWidth =
3962  BaseType->isVectorTy()
3963  ? cast<FixedVectorType>(BaseType)->getNumElements()
3964  : 0;
3965 
3966  ArrayRef<Constant *> Indices(Elts.begin() + 1, Elts.end());
3967  for (Constant *Val : Indices) {
3968  Type *ValTy = Val->getType();
3969  if (!ValTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3970  return error(ID.Loc, "getelementptr index must be an integer");
3971  if (auto *ValVTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(ValTy)) {
3972  unsigned ValNumEl = cast<FixedVectorType>(ValVTy)->getNumElements();
3973  if (GEPWidth && (ValNumEl != GEPWidth))
3974  return error(
3975  ID.Loc,
3976  "getelementptr vector index has a wrong number of elements");
3977  // GEPWidth may have been unknown because the base is a scalar,
3978  // but it is known now.
3979  GEPWidth = ValNumEl;
3980  }
3981  }
3982 
3983  SmallPtrSet<Type*, 4> Visited;
3984  if (!Indices.empty() && !Ty->isSized(&Visited))
3985  return error(ID.Loc, "base element of getelementptr must be sized");
3986 
3987  if (!GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(Ty, Indices))
3988  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid getelementptr indices");
3989 
3990  if (InRangeOp) {
3991  if (*InRangeOp == 0)
3992  return error(ID.Loc,
3993  "inrange keyword may not appear on pointer operand");
3994  --*InRangeOp;
3995  }
3996 
3997  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Ty, Elts[0], Indices,
3998  InBounds, InRangeOp);
3999  } else if (Opc == Instruction::Select) {
4000  if (Elts.size() != 3)
4001  return error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to select");
4002  if (const char *Reason = SelectInst::areInvalidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1],
4003  Elts[2]))
4004  return error(ID.Loc, Reason);
4005  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getSelect(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]);
4006  } else if (Opc == Instruction::ShuffleVector) {
4007  if (Elts.size() != 3)
4008  return error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to shufflevector");
4009  if (!ShuffleVectorInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]))
4010  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid operands to shufflevector");
4011  SmallVector<int, 16> Mask;
4012  ShuffleVectorInst::getShuffleMask(cast<Constant>(Elts[2]), Mask);
4013  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(Elts[0], Elts[1], Mask);
4014  } else if (Opc == Instruction::ExtractElement) {
4015  if (Elts.size() != 2)
4016  return error(ID.Loc, "expected two operands to extractelement");
4017  if (!ExtractElementInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1]))
4018  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid extractelement operands");
4019  ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getExtractElement(Elts[0], Elts[1]);
4020  } else {
4021  assert(Opc == Instruction::InsertElement && "Unknown opcode");
4022  if (Elts.size() != 3)
4023  return error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to insertelement");
4024  if (!InsertElementInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]))
4025  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid insertelement operands");
4026  ID.ConstantVal =
4027  ConstantExpr::getInsertElement(Elts[0], Elts[1],Elts[2]);
4028  }
4029 
4030  ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
4031  return false;
4032  }
4033  }
4034 
4035  Lex.Lex();
4036  return false;
4037 }

4039 /// parseGlobalValue - parse a global value with the specified type.
4040 bool LLParser::parseGlobalValue(Type *Ty, Constant *&C) {
4041  C = nullptr;
4042  ValID ID;
4043  Value *V = nullptr;
4044  bool Parsed = parseValID(ID, /*PFS=*/nullptr, Ty) ||
4045  convertValIDToValue(Ty, ID, V, nullptr);
4046  if (V && !(C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V)))
4047  return error(ID.Loc, "global values must be constants");
4048  return Parsed;
4049 }

4056 bool LLParser::parseOptionalComdat(StringRef GlobalName, Comdat *&C) {
4057  C = nullptr;
4058 
4059  LocTy KwLoc = Lex.getLoc();
4060  if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_comdat))
4061  return false;
4062 
4063  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::lparen)) {
4064  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::ComdatVar)
4065  return tokError("expected comdat variable");
4066  C = getComdat(Lex.getStrVal(), Lex.getLoc());
4067  Lex.Lex();
4068  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' after comdat var"))
4069  return true;
4070  } else {
4071  if (GlobalName.empty())
4072  return tokError("comdat cannot be unnamed");
4073  C = getComdat(std::string(GlobalName), KwLoc);
4074  }
4075 
4076  return false;
4077 }

4079 /// parseGlobalValueVector
4080 /// ::= /*empty*/
4081 /// ::= [inrange] TypeAndValue (',' [inrange] TypeAndValue)*
4082 bool LLParser::parseGlobalValueVector(SmallVectorImpl<Constant *> &Elts,
4083  std::optional<unsigned> *InRangeOp) {
4084  // Empty list.
4085  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rbrace ||
4086  Lex.getKind() == lltok::rsquare ||
4087  Lex.getKind() == lltok::greater ||
4088  Lex.getKind() == lltok::rparen)
4089  return false;
4090 
4091  do {
4092  if (InRangeOp && !*InRangeOp && EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inrange))
4093  *InRangeOp = Elts.size();
4094 
4095  Constant *C;
4096  if (parseGlobalTypeAndValue(C))
4097  return true;
4098  Elts.push_back(C);
4099  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
4100 
4101  return false;
4102 }

4104 bool LLParser::parseMDTuple(MDNode *&MD, bool IsDistinct) {
4105  SmallVector<Metadata *, 16> Elts;
4106  if (parseMDNodeVector(Elts))
4107  return true;
4108 
4109  MD = (IsDistinct ? MDTuple::getDistinct : MDTuple::get)(Context, Elts);
4110  return false;
4111 }

4117 bool LLParser::parseMDNode(MDNode *&N) {

4119  return parseSpecializedMDNode(N);
4120 
4121  return parseToken(lltok::exclaim, "expected '!' here") || parseMDNodeTail(N);
4122 }

4124 bool LLParser::parseMDNodeTail(MDNode *&N) {
4125  // !{ ... }
4126  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::lbrace)
4127  return parseMDTuple(N);
4128 
4129  // !42
4130  return parseMDNodeID(N);
4131 }

4135 /// Structure to represent an optional metadata field.
4136 template <class FieldTy> struct MDFieldImpl {
4137  typedef MDFieldImpl ImplTy;
4138  FieldTy Val;
4139  bool Seen;
4140 
4141  void assign(FieldTy Val) {
4142  Seen = true;
4143  this->Val = std::move(Val);
4144  }
4145 
4146  explicit MDFieldImpl(FieldTy Default)
4147  : Val(std::move(Default)), Seen(false) {}
4148 };
4149 
4150 /// Structure to represent an optional metadata field that
4151 /// can be of either type (A or B) and encapsulates the
4152 /// MD<typeofA>Field and MD<typeofB>Field structs, so not
4153 /// to reimplement the specifics for representing each Field.
4154 template <class FieldTypeA, class FieldTypeB> struct MDEitherFieldImpl {
4155  typedef MDEitherFieldImpl<FieldTypeA, FieldTypeB> ImplTy;
4156  FieldTypeA A;
4157  FieldTypeB B;
4158  bool Seen;
4159 
4160  enum {
4161  IsInvalid = 0,
4162  IsTypeA = 1,
4163  IsTypeB = 2
4164  } WhatIs;
4165 
4166  void assign(FieldTypeA A) {
4167  Seen = true;
4168  this->A = std::move(A);
4169  WhatIs = IsTypeA;
4170  }
4171 
4172  void assign(FieldTypeB B) {
4173  Seen = true;
4174  this->B = std::move(B);
4175  WhatIs = IsTypeB;
4176  }
4177 
4178  explicit MDEitherFieldImpl(FieldTypeA DefaultA, FieldTypeB DefaultB)
4179  : A(std::move(DefaultA)), B(std::move(DefaultB)), Seen(false),
4180  WhatIs(IsInvalid) {}
4181 };

4318 bool LLParser::parseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name,
4319  MDUnsignedField &Result) {

4321  return tokError("expected unsigned integer");
4322 
4323  auto &U = Lex.getAPSIntVal();

4325  return tokError("value for '" + Name + "' too large, limit is " +
4326  Twine(Result.Max));

4328  assert(Result.Val <= Result.Max && "Expected value in range");
4329  Lex.Lex();

4331 }

4492 /// DIFlagField
4493 /// ::= uint32
4494 /// ::= DIFlagVector
4495 /// ::= DIFlagVector '|' DIFlagFwdDecl '|' uint32 '|' DIFlagPublic
4496 template <>
4497 bool LLParser::parseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, DIFlagField &Result) {
4498 
4499  // parser for a single flag.
4500  auto parseFlag = [&](DINode::DIFlags &Val) {
4501  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt && !Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned()) {
4502  uint32_t TempVal = static_cast<uint32_t>(Val);
4503  bool Res = parseUInt32(TempVal);
4504  Val = static_cast<DINode::DIFlags>(TempVal);
4505  return Res;
4506  }
4507 
4508  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::DIFlag)
4509  return tokError("expected debug info flag");
4510 
4511  Val = DINode::getFlag(Lex.getStrVal());
4512  if (!Val)
4513  return tokError(Twine("invalid debug info flag '") + Lex.getStrVal() +
4514  "'");
4515  Lex.Lex();
4516  return false;
4517  };
4518 
4519  // parse the flags and combine them together.
4520  DINode::DIFlags Combined = DINode::FlagZero;
4521  do {
4522  DINode::DIFlags Val;
4523  if (parseFlag(Val))
4524  return true;
4525  Combined |= Val;
4526  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::bar));
4527 
4528  Result.assign(Combined);
4529  return false;
4530 }
4531 
4532 /// DISPFlagField
4533 /// ::= uint32
4534 /// ::= DISPFlagVector
4535 /// ::= DISPFlagVector '|' DISPFlag* '|' uint32
4536 template <>
4537 bool LLParser::parseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, DISPFlagField &Result) {
4538 
4539  // parser for a single flag.
4540  auto parseFlag = [&](DISubprogram::DISPFlags &Val) {
4541  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt && !Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned()) {
4542  uint32_t TempVal = static_cast<uint32_t>(Val);
4543  bool Res = parseUInt32(TempVal);
4544  Val = static_cast<DISubprogram::DISPFlags>(TempVal);
4545  return Res;
4546  }
4547 
4548  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::DISPFlag)
4549  return tokError("expected debug info flag");
4550 
4551  Val = DISubprogram::getFlag(Lex.getStrVal());
4552  if (!Val)
4553  return tokError(Twine("invalid subprogram debug info flag '") +
4554  Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
4555  Lex.Lex();
4556  return false;
4557  };
4558 
4559  // parse the flags and combine them together.
4560  DISubprogram::DISPFlags Combined = DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
4561  do {
4562  DISubprogram::DISPFlags Val;
4563  if (parseFlag(Val))
4564  return true;
4565  Combined |= Val;
4566  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::bar));
4567 
4568  Result.assign(Combined);
4569  return false;
4570 }

4572 template <>
4573 bool LLParser::parseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, MDSignedField &Result) {
4574  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt)
4575  return tokError("expected signed integer");
4576 
4577  auto &S = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
4578  if (S < Result.Min)
4579  return tokError("value for '" + Name + "' too small, limit is " +
4580  Twine(Result.Min));
4581  if (S > Result.Max)
4582  return tokError("value for '" + Name + "' too large, limit is " +
4583  Twine(Result.Max));
4584  Result.assign(S.getExtValue());
4585  assert(Result.Val >= Result.Min && "Expected value in range");
4586  assert(Result.Val <= Result.Max && "Expected value in range");
4587  Lex.Lex();
4588  return false;
4589 }

4602  }

4604  return false;

4625 template <>
4626 bool LLParser::parseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name,
4627  MDSignedOrMDField &Result) {
4628  // Try to parse a signed int.
4629  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt) {
4630  MDSignedField Res = Result.A;
4631  if (!parseMDField(Loc, Name, Res)) {
4632  Result.assign(Res);
4633  return false;
4634  }
4635  return true;
4636  }
4637 
4638  // Otherwise, try to parse as an MDField.
4639  MDField Res = Result.B;
4640  if (!parseMDField(Loc, Name, Res)) {
4641  Result.assign(Res);
4642  return false;
4643  }
4644 
4645  return true;
4646 }

4659  return false;

4702 template <class ParserTy>
4703 bool LLParser::parseMDFieldsImpl(ParserTy ParseField, LocTy &ClosingLoc) {
4704  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
4705  Lex.Lex();
4706 
4707  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
4708  return true;
4709  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen)
4710  if (parseMDFieldsImplBody(ParseField))
4711  return true;
4712 
4713  ClosingLoc = Lex.getLoc();
4714  return parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here");

4727 bool LLParser::parseSpecializedMDNode(MDNode *&N, bool IsDistinct) {
4728  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
4729 
4730 #define HANDLE_SPECIALIZED_MDNODE_LEAF(CLASS) \
4731  if (Lex.getStrVal() == #CLASS) \
4732  return parse##CLASS(N, IsDistinct);
4733 #include "llvm/IR/Metadata.def"
4734 
4735  return tokError("expected metadata type");
4736 }
4737 
4738 #define DECLARE_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT) TYPE NAME INIT
4739 #define NOP_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT)
4740 #define REQUIRE_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT) \
4741  if (!NAME.Seen) \
4742  return error(ClosingLoc, "missing required field '" #NAME "'");
4743 #define PARSE_MD_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, DEFAULT) \
4744  if (Lex.getStrVal() == #NAME) \
4745  return parseMDField(#NAME, NAME);
4746 #define PARSE_MD_FIELDS() \
4747  VISIT_MD_FIELDS(DECLARE_FIELD, DECLARE_FIELD) \
4748  do { \
4749  LocTy ClosingLoc; \
4750  if (parseMDFieldsImpl( \
4751  [&]() -> bool { \
4752  VISIT_MD_FIELDS(PARSE_MD_FIELD, PARSE_MD_FIELD) \
4753  return tokError(Twine("invalid field '") + Lex.getStrVal() + \
4754  "'"); \
4755  }, \
4756  ClosingLoc)) \
4757  return true; \
4758  VISIT_MD_FIELDS(NOP_FIELD, REQUIRE_FIELD) \
4759  } while (false)
4760 #define GET_OR_DISTINCT(CLASS, ARGS) \
4761  (IsDistinct ? CLASS::getDistinct ARGS : CLASS::get ARGS)
4762 
4763 /// parseDILocationFields:
4764 /// ::= !DILocation(line: 43, column: 8, scope: !5, inlinedAt: !6,
4765 /// isImplicitCode: true)
4766 bool LLParser::parseDILocation(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4767 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4768  OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4769  OPTIONAL(column, ColumnField, ); \
4770  REQUIRED(scope, MDField, (/* AllowNull */ false)); \
4771  OPTIONAL(inlinedAt, MDField, ); \
4772  OPTIONAL(isImplicitCode, MDBoolField, (false));
4773  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4774 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4775 
4776  Result =
4777  GET_OR_DISTINCT(DILocation, (Context, line.Val, column.Val, scope.Val,
4778  inlinedAt.Val, isImplicitCode.Val));
4779  return false;
4780 }

4815 /// parseDISubrange:
4816 /// ::= !DISubrange(count: 30, lowerBound: 2)
4817 /// ::= !DISubrange(count: !node, lowerBound: 2)
4818 /// ::= !DISubrange(lowerBound: !node1, upperBound: !node2, stride: !node3)
4819 bool LLParser::parseDISubrange(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4820 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4821  OPTIONAL(count, MDSignedOrMDField, (-1, -1, INT64_MAX, false)); \
4822  OPTIONAL(lowerBound, MDSignedOrMDField, ); \
4823  OPTIONAL(upperBound, MDSignedOrMDField, ); \
4824  OPTIONAL(stride, MDSignedOrMDField, );
4825  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4826 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4827 
4828  Metadata *Count = nullptr;
4829  Metadata *LowerBound = nullptr;
4830  Metadata *UpperBound = nullptr;
4831  Metadata *Stride = nullptr;
4832 
4833  auto convToMetadata = [&](MDSignedOrMDField Bound) -> Metadata * {
4834  if (Bound.isMDSignedField())
4835  return ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::getSigned(
4836  Type::getInt64Ty(Context), Bound.getMDSignedValue()));
4837  if (Bound.isMDField())
4838  return Bound.getMDFieldValue();
4839  return nullptr;
4840  };
4841 
4842  Count = convToMetadata(count);
4843  LowerBound = convToMetadata(lowerBound);
4844  UpperBound = convToMetadata(upperBound);
4845  Stride = convToMetadata(stride);
4846 
4847  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DISubrange,
4848  (Context, Count, LowerBound, UpperBound, Stride));
4849 
4850  return false;
4851 }

4886 /// parseDIEnumerator:
4887 /// ::= !DIEnumerator(value: 30, isUnsigned: true, name: "SomeKind")
4888 bool LLParser::parseDIEnumerator(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4889 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4890  REQUIRED(name, MDStringField, ); \
4891  REQUIRED(value, MDAPSIntField, ); \
4892  OPTIONAL(isUnsigned, MDBoolField, (false));
4893  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4894 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4895 
4896  if (isUnsigned.Val && value.Val.isNegative())
4897  return tokError("unsigned enumerator with negative value");
4898 
4899  APSInt Value(value.Val);
4900  // Add a leading zero so that unsigned values with the msb set are not
4901  // mistaken for negative values when used for signed enumerators.
4902  if (!isUnsigned.Val && value.Val.isUnsigned() && value.Val.isSignBitSet())
4903  Value = Value.zext(Value.getBitWidth() + 1);
4904 
4905  Result =
4906  GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIEnumerator, (Context, Value, isUnsigned.Val, name.Val));
4907 
4908  return false;
4909 }

4987 bool LLParser::parseDICompositeType(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4988 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4989  REQUIRED(tag, DwarfTagField, ); \
4990  OPTIONAL(name, MDStringField, ); \
4991  OPTIONAL(file, MDField, ); \
4992  OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4993  OPTIONAL(scope, MDField, ); \
4994  OPTIONAL(baseType, MDField, ); \
4995  OPTIONAL(size, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4996  OPTIONAL(align, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT32_MAX)); \
4997  OPTIONAL(offset, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4998  OPTIONAL(flags, DIFlagField, ); \
4999  OPTIONAL(elements, MDField, ); \
5000  OPTIONAL(runtimeLang, DwarfLangField, ); \
5001  OPTIONAL(vtableHolder, MDField, ); \
5002  OPTIONAL(templateParams, MDField, ); \
5003  OPTIONAL(identifier, MDStringField, ); \
5004  OPTIONAL(discriminator, MDField, ); \
5005  OPTIONAL(dataLocation, MDField, ); \
5006  OPTIONAL(associated, MDField, ); \
5007  OPTIONAL(allocated, MDField, ); \
5008  OPTIONAL(rank, MDSignedOrMDField, ); \
5009  OPTIONAL(annotations, MDField, );
5010  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
5011 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
5012 
5013  Metadata *Rank = nullptr;
5014  if (rank.isMDSignedField())
5015  Rank = ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::getSigned(
5016  Type::getInt64Ty(Context), rank.getMDSignedValue()));
5017  else if (rank.isMDField())
5018  Rank = rank.getMDFieldValue();
5019 
5020  // If this has an identifier try to build an ODR type.
5021  if (identifier.Val)
5022  if (auto *CT = DICompositeType::buildODRType(
5023  Context, *identifier.Val, tag.Val, name.Val, file.Val, line.Val,
5024  scope.Val, baseType.Val, size.Val, align.Val, offset.Val, flags.Val,
5025  elements.Val, runtimeLang.Val, vtableHolder.Val, templateParams.Val,
5026  discriminator.Val, dataLocation.Val, associated.Val, allocated.Val,
5027  Rank, annotations.Val)) {
5028  Result = CT;
5029  return false;
5030  }
5031 
5032  // Create a new node, and save it in the context if it belongs in the type
5033  // map.
5034  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
5035  DICompositeType,
5036  (Context, tag.Val, name.Val, file.Val, line.Val, scope.Val, baseType.Val,
5037  size.Val, align.Val, offset.Val, flags.Val, elements.Val,
5038  runtimeLang.Val, vtableHolder.Val, templateParams.Val, identifier.Val,
5039  discriminator.Val, dataLocation.Val, associated.Val, allocated.Val, Rank,
5040  annotations.Val));
5041  return false;
5042 }

5057 /// parseDIFileType:
5058 /// ::= !DIFileType(filename: "path/to/file", directory: "/path/to/dir",
5059 /// checksumkind: CSK_MD5,
5060 /// checksum: "000102030405060708090a0b0c0d0e0f",
5061 /// source: "source file contents")
5062 bool LLParser::parseDIFile(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
5063  // The default constructed value for checksumkind is required, but will never
5064  // be used, as the parser checks if the field was actually Seen before using
5065  // the Val.
5066 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
5067  REQUIRED(filename, MDStringField, ); \
5068  REQUIRED(directory, MDStringField, ); \
5069  OPTIONAL(checksumkind, ChecksumKindField, (DIFile::CSK_MD5)); \
5070  OPTIONAL(checksum, MDStringField, ); \
5071  OPTIONAL(source, MDStringField, );
5072  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
5073 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
5074 
5075  std::optional<DIFile::ChecksumInfo<MDString *>> OptChecksum;
5076  if (checksumkind.Seen && checksum.Seen)
5077  OptChecksum.emplace(checksumkind.Val, checksum.Val);
5078  else if (checksumkind.Seen || checksum.Seen)
5079  return Lex.Error("'checksumkind' and 'checksum' must be provided together");
5080 
5081  MDString *Source = nullptr;
5082  if (source.Seen)
5083  Source = source.Val;
5084  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
5085  DIFile, (Context, filename.Val, directory.Val, OptChecksum, Source));
5086  return false;
5087 }

5133 /// parseDISubprogram:
5134 /// ::= !DISubprogram(scope: !0, name: "foo", linkageName: "_Zfoo",
5135 /// file: !1, line: 7, type: !2, isLocal: false,
5136 /// isDefinition: true, scopeLine: 8, containingType: !3,
5137 /// virtuality: DW_VIRTUALTIY_pure_virtual,
5138 /// virtualIndex: 10, thisAdjustment: 4, flags: 11,
5139 /// spFlags: 10, isOptimized: false, templateParams: !4,
5140 /// declaration: !5, retainedNodes: !6, thrownTypes: !7,
5141 /// annotations: !8)
5142 bool LLParser::parseDISubprogram(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
5143  auto Loc = Lex.getLoc();
5144 #define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
5145  OPTIONAL(scope, MDField, ); \
5146  OPTIONAL(name, MDStringField, ); \
5147  OPTIONAL(linkageName, MDStringField, ); \
5148  OPTIONAL(file, MDField, ); \
5149  OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
5150  OPTIONAL(type, MDField, ); \
5151  OPTIONAL(isLocal, MDBoolField, ); \
5152  OPTIONAL(isDefinition, MDBoolField, (true)); \
5153  OPTIONAL(scopeLine, LineField, ); \
5154  OPTIONAL(containingType, MDField, ); \
5155  OPTIONAL(virtuality, DwarfVirtualityField, ); \
5156  OPTIONAL(virtualIndex, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT32_MAX)); \
5157  OPTIONAL(thisAdjustment, MDSignedField, (0, INT32_MIN, INT32_MAX)); \
5158  OPTIONAL(flags, DIFlagField, ); \
5159  OPTIONAL(spFlags, DISPFlagField, ); \
5160  OPTIONAL(isOptimized, MDBoolField, ); \
5161  OPTIONAL(unit, MDField, ); \
5162  OPTIONAL(templateParams, MDField, ); \
5163  OPTIONAL(declaration, MDField, ); \
5164  OPTIONAL(retainedNodes, MDField, ); \
5165  OPTIONAL(thrownTypes, MDField, ); \
5166  OPTIONAL(annotations, MDField, ); \
5167  OPTIONAL(targetFuncName, MDStringField, );
5168  PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
5169 #undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
5170 
5171  // An explicit spFlags field takes precedence over individual fields in
5172  // older IR versions.
5173  DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags =
5174  spFlags.Seen ? spFlags.Val
5175  : DISubprogram::toSPFlags(isLocal.Val, isDefinition.Val,
5176  isOptimized.Val, virtuality.Val);
5177  if ((SPFlags & DISubprogram::SPFlagDefinition) && !IsDistinct)
5178  return Lex.Error(
5179  Loc,
5180  "missing 'distinct', required for !DISubprogram that is a Definition");
5181  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
5182  DISubprogram,
5183  (Context, scope.Val, name.Val, linkageName.Val, file.Val, line.Val,
5184  type.Val, scopeLine.Val, containingType.Val, virtualIndex.Val,
5185  thisAdjustment.Val, flags.Val, SPFlags, unit.Val, templateParams.Val,
5186  declaration.Val, retainedNodes.Val, thrownTypes.Val, annotations.Val,
5187  targetFuncName.Val));
5188  return false;
5189 }

5402  annotations.Val));
5403  return false;
5404 }

5422 /// parseDIExpression:
5423 /// ::= !DIExpression(0, 7, -1)
5424 bool LLParser::parseDIExpression(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
5425  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
5426  Lex.Lex();
5427 
5428  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
5429  return true;
5430 
5431  SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Elements;
5432  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen)
5433  do {
5434  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::DwarfOp) {
5435  if (unsigned Op = dwarf::getOperationEncoding(Lex.getStrVal())) {
5436  Lex.Lex();
5437  Elements.push_back(Op);
5438  continue;
5439  }
5440  return tokError(Twine("invalid DWARF op '") + Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
5441  }
5442 
5443  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::DwarfAttEncoding) {
5444  if (unsigned Op = dwarf::getAttributeEncoding(Lex.getStrVal())) {
5445  Lex.Lex();
5446  Elements.push_back(Op);
5447  continue;
5448  }
5449  return tokError(Twine("invalid DWARF attribute encoding '") +
5450  Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
5451  }
5452 
5453  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt || Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned())
5454  return tokError("expected unsigned integer");
5455 
5456  auto &U = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
5457  if (U.ugt(UINT64_MAX))
5458  return tokError("element too large, limit is " + Twine(UINT64_MAX));
5459  Elements.push_back(U.getZExtValue());
5460  Lex.Lex();
5461  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
5462 
5463  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
5464  return true;
5465 
5466  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIExpression, (Context, Elements));
5467  return false;
5468 }
5469 
5470 bool LLParser::parseDIArgList(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
5471  return parseDIArgList(Result, IsDistinct, nullptr);
5472 }
5473 /// ParseDIArgList:
5474 /// ::= !DIArgList(i32 7, i64 %0)
5475 bool LLParser::parseDIArgList(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct,
5476  PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5477  assert(PFS && "Expected valid function state");
5478  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
5479  Lex.Lex();
5480 
5481  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
5482  return true;
5483 
5484  SmallVector<ValueAsMetadata *, 4> Args;
5485  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen)
5486  do {
5487  Metadata *MD;
5488  if (parseValueAsMetadata(MD, "expected value-as-metadata operand", PFS))
5489  return true;
5490  Args.push_back(dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(MD));
5491  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
5492 
5493  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
5494  return true;
5495 
5496  Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIArgList, (Context, Args));
5497  return false;
5498 }

5562 /// parseMetadataAsValue
5563 /// ::= metadata i32 %local
5564 /// ::= metadata i32 @global
5565 /// ::= metadata i32 7
5566 /// ::= metadata !0
5567 /// ::= metadata !{...}
5568 /// ::= metadata !"string"
5569 bool LLParser::parseMetadataAsValue(Value *&V, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
5570  // Note: the type 'metadata' has already been parsed.
5571  Metadata *MD;
5572  if (parseMetadata(MD, &PFS))
5573  return true;
5574 
5575  V = MetadataAsValue::get(Context, MD);
5576  return false;

5579 /// parseValueAsMetadata
5580 /// ::= i32 %local
5581 /// ::= i32 @global
5582 /// ::= i32 7
5583 bool LLParser::parseValueAsMetadata(Metadata *&MD, const Twine &TypeMsg,
5584  PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5585  Type *Ty;
5586  LocTy Loc;
5587  if (parseType(Ty, TypeMsg, Loc))
5588  return true;
5589  if (Ty->isMetadataTy())
5590  return error(Loc, "invalid metadata-value-metadata roundtrip");
5591 
5592  Value *V;
5593  if (parseValue(Ty, V, PFS))
5594  return true;
5595 
5596  MD = ValueAsMetadata::get(V);
5597  return false;
5598 }
5599 
5600 /// parseMetadata
5601 /// ::= i32 %local
5602 /// ::= i32 @global
5603 /// ::= i32 7
5604 /// ::= !42
5605 /// ::= !{...}
5606 /// ::= !"string"
5607 /// ::= !DILocation(...)
5608 bool LLParser::parseMetadata(Metadata *&MD, PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5609  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
5610  MDNode *N;
5611  // DIArgLists are a special case, as they are a list of ValueAsMetadata and
5612  // so parsing this requires a Function State.
5613  if (Lex.getStrVal() == "DIArgList") {
5614  if (parseDIArgList(N, false, PFS))
5615  return true;
5616  } else if (parseSpecializedMDNode(N)) {
5617  return true;
5618  }
5619  MD = N;
5620  return false;
5621  }
5622 
5623  // ValueAsMetadata:
5624  // <type> <value>
5625  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::exclaim)
5626  return parseValueAsMetadata(MD, "expected metadata operand", PFS);
5627 
5628  // '!'.
5629  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::exclaim && "Expected '!' here");
5630  Lex.Lex();
5631 
5632  // MDString:
5633  // ::= '!' STRINGCONSTANT
5634  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::StringConstant) {
5635  MDString *S;
5636  if (parseMDString(S))
5637  return true;
5638  MD = S;
5639  return false;
5640  }
5641 
5642  // MDNode:
5643  // !{ ... }
5644  // !7
5645  MDNode *N;
5646  if (parseMDNodeTail(N))
5647  return true;
5648  MD = N;
5649  return false;
5650 }

5655 
5656 bool LLParser::convertValIDToValue(Type *Ty, ValID &ID, Value *&V,
5657  PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5658  if (Ty->isFunctionTy())
5659  return error(ID.Loc, "functions are not values, refer to them as pointers");
5660 
5661  switch (ID.Kind) {
5662  case ValID::t_LocalID:
5663  if (!PFS)
5664  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid use of function-local name");
5665  V = PFS->getVal(ID.UIntVal, Ty, ID.Loc);
5666  return V == nullptr;
5667  case ValID::t_LocalName:
5668  if (!PFS)
5669  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid use of function-local name");
5670  V = PFS->getVal(ID.StrVal, Ty, ID.Loc);
5671  return V == nullptr;
5672  case ValID::t_InlineAsm: {
5673  if (!ID.FTy)
5674  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for inline asm constraint string");
5675  if (Error Err = InlineAsm::verify(ID.FTy, ID.StrVal2))
5676  return error(ID.Loc, toString(std::move(Err)));
5677  V = InlineAsm::get(
5678  ID.FTy, ID.StrVal, ID.StrVal2, ID.UIntVal & 1, (ID.UIntVal >> 1) & 1,
5679  InlineAsm::AsmDialect((ID.UIntVal >> 2) & 1), (ID.UIntVal >> 3) & 1);
5680  return false;
5681  }
5682  case ValID::t_GlobalName:
5683  V = getGlobalVal(ID.StrVal, Ty, ID.Loc);
5684  if (V && ID.NoCFI)
5685  V = NoCFIValue::get(cast<GlobalValue>(V));
5686  return V == nullptr;
5687  case ValID::t_GlobalID:
5688  V = getGlobalVal(ID.UIntVal, Ty, ID.Loc);
5689  if (V && ID.NoCFI)
5690  V = NoCFIValue::get(cast<GlobalValue>(V));
5691  return V == nullptr;
5692  case ValID::t_APSInt:
5693  if (!Ty->isIntegerTy())
5694  return error(ID.Loc, "integer constant must have integer type");
5695  ID.APSIntVal = ID.APSIntVal.extOrTrunc(Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
5696  V = ConstantInt::get(Context, ID.APSIntVal);
5697  return false;
5698  case ValID::t_APFloat:
5699  if (!Ty->isFloatingPointTy() ||
5700  !ConstantFP::isValueValidForType(Ty, ID.APFloatVal))
5701  return error(ID.Loc, "floating point constant invalid for type");
5702 
5703  // The lexer has no type info, so builds all half, bfloat, float, and double
5704  // FP constants as double. Fix this here. Long double does not need this.
5705  if (&ID.APFloatVal.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble()) {
5706  // Check for signaling before potentially converting and losing that info.
5707  bool IsSNAN = ID.APFloatVal.isSignaling();
5708  bool Ignored;
5709  if (Ty->isHalfTy())
5710  ID.APFloatVal.convert(APFloat::IEEEhalf(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
5711  &Ignored);
5712  else if (Ty->isBFloatTy())
5713  ID.APFloatVal.convert(APFloat::BFloat(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
5714  &Ignored);
5715  else if (Ty->isFloatTy())
5716  ID.APFloatVal.convert(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
5717  &Ignored);
5718  if (IsSNAN) {
5719  // The convert call above may quiet an SNaN, so manufacture another
5720  // SNaN. The bitcast works because the payload (significand) parameter
5721  // is truncated to fit.
5722  APInt Payload = ID.APFloatVal.bitcastToAPInt();
5723  ID.APFloatVal = APFloat::getSNaN(ID.APFloatVal.getSemantics(),
5724  ID.APFloatVal.isNegative(), &Payload);
5725  }
5726  }
5727  V = ConstantFP::get(Context, ID.APFloatVal);
5728 
5729  if (V->getType() != Ty)
5730  return error(ID.Loc, "floating point constant does not have type '" +
5731  getTypeString(Ty) + "'");
5732 
5733  return false;
5734  case ValID::t_Null:
5735  if (!Ty->isPointerTy())
5736  return error(ID.Loc, "null must be a pointer type");
5737  V = ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<PointerType>(Ty));
5738  return false;
5739  case ValID::t_Undef:
5740  // FIXME: LabelTy should not be a first-class type.
5741  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType() || Ty->isLabelTy())
5742  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for undef constant");
5743  V = UndefValue::get(Ty);
5744  return false;
5745  case ValID::t_EmptyArray:
5746  if (!Ty->isArrayTy() || cast<ArrayType>(Ty)->getNumElements() != 0)
5747  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid empty array initializer");
5748  V = UndefValue::get(Ty);
5749  return false;
5750  case ValID::t_Zero:
5751  // FIXME: LabelTy should not be a first-class type.
5752  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType() || Ty->isLabelTy())
5753  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for null constant");
5754  if (auto *TETy = dyn_cast<TargetExtType>(Ty))
5755  if (!TETy->hasProperty(TargetExtType::HasZeroInit))
5756  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for null constant");
5757  V = Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
5758  return false;
5759  case ValID::t_None:
5760  if (!Ty->isTokenTy())
5761  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for none constant");
5762  V = Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
5763  return false;
5764  case ValID::t_Poison:
5765  // FIXME: LabelTy should not be a first-class type.
5766  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType() || Ty->isLabelTy())
5767  return error(ID.Loc, "invalid type for poison constant");
5768  V = PoisonValue::get(Ty);
5769  return false;
5770  case ValID::t_Constant:
5771  if (ID.ConstantVal->getType() != Ty)
5772  return error(ID.Loc, "constant expression type mismatch: got type '" +
5773  getTypeString(ID.ConstantVal->getType()) +
5774  "' but expected '" + getTypeString(Ty) + "'");
5775  V = ID.ConstantVal;
5776  return false;
5777  case ValID::t_ConstantStruct:
5778  case ValID::t_PackedConstantStruct:
5779  if (StructType *ST = dyn_cast<StructType>(Ty)) {
5780  if (ST->getNumElements() != ID.UIntVal)
5781  return error(ID.Loc,
5782  "initializer with struct type has wrong # elements");
5783  if (ST->isPacked() != (ID.Kind == ValID::t_PackedConstantStruct))
5784  return error(ID.Loc, "packed'ness of initializer and type don't match");
5785 
5786  // Verify that the elements are compatible with the structtype.
5787  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ID.UIntVal; i != e; ++i)
5788  if (ID.ConstantStructElts[i]->getType() != ST->getElementType(i))
5789  return error(
5790  ID.Loc,
5791  "element " + Twine(i) +
5792  " of struct initializer doesn't match struct element type");
5793 
5794  V = ConstantStruct::get(
5795  ST, ArrayRef(ID.ConstantStructElts.get(), ID.UIntVal));
5796  } else
5797  return error(ID.Loc, "constant expression type mismatch");
5798  return false;
5799  }
5800  llvm_unreachable("Invalid ValID");
5801 }
5802 
5803 bool LLParser::parseConstantValue(Type *Ty, Constant *&C) {
5804  C = nullptr;
5805  ValID ID;
5806  auto Loc = Lex.getLoc();
5807  if (parseValID(ID, /*PFS=*/nullptr))
5808  return true;
5809  switch (ID.Kind) {
5810  case ValID::t_APSInt:
5811  case ValID::t_APFloat:
5812  case ValID::t_Undef:
5813  case ValID::t_Constant:
5814  case ValID::t_ConstantStruct:
5815  case ValID::t_PackedConstantStruct: {
5816  Value *V;
5817  if (convertValIDToValue(Ty, ID, V, /*PFS=*/nullptr))
5818  return true;
5819  assert(isa<Constant>(V) && "Expected a constant value");
5820  C = cast<Constant>(V);
5821  return false;
5822  }
5823  case ValID::t_Null:
5824  C = Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
5825  return false;
5826  default:
5827  return error(Loc, "expected a constant value");
5828  }
5829 }

5832  V = nullptr;
5833  ValID ID;
5834  return parseValID(ID, PFS, Ty) ||
5835  convertValIDToValue(Ty, ID, V, PFS);
5836 }

5843 bool LLParser::parseTypeAndBasicBlock(BasicBlock *&BB, LocTy &Loc,
