5855 /// FunctionHeader
5856 /// ::= OptionalLinkage OptionalPreemptionSpecifier OptionalVisibility
5857 /// OptionalCallingConv OptRetAttrs OptUnnamedAddr Type GlobalName
5858 /// '(' ArgList ')' OptAddrSpace OptFuncAttrs OptSection OptionalAlign
5859 /// OptGC OptionalPrefix OptionalPrologue OptPersonalityFn
5860 bool LLParser::parseFunctionHeader(Function *&Fn, bool IsDefine) {
5861  // parse the linkage.
5862  LocTy LinkageLoc = Lex.getLoc();
5863  unsigned Linkage;
5864  unsigned Visibility;
5865  unsigned DLLStorageClass;
5866  bool DSOLocal;
5867  AttrBuilder RetAttrs(M->getContext());
5868  unsigned CC;
5869  bool HasLinkage;
5870  Type *RetType = nullptr;
5871  LocTy RetTypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
5872  if (parseOptionalLinkage(Linkage, HasLinkage, Visibility, DLLStorageClass,
5873  DSOLocal) ||
5874  parseOptionalCallingConv(CC) || parseOptionalReturnAttrs(RetAttrs) ||
5875  parseType(RetType, RetTypeLoc, true /*void allowed*/))
5876  return true;
5877 
5878  // Verify that the linkage is ok.
5879  switch ((GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)Linkage) {
5880  case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
5881  break; // always ok.
5882  case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage:
5883  if (IsDefine)
5884  return error(LinkageLoc, "invalid linkage for function definition");
5885  break;
5886  case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
5887  case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
5888  case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage:
5889  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage:
5890  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
5891  case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage:
5892  case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
5893  if (!IsDefine)
5894  return error(LinkageLoc, "invalid linkage for function declaration");
5895  break;
5896  case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage:
5897  case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage:
5898  return error(LinkageLoc, "invalid function linkage type");
5899  }
5900 
5901  if (!isValidVisibilityForLinkage(Visibility, Linkage))
5902  return error(LinkageLoc,
5903  "symbol with local linkage must have default visibility");
5904 
5905  if (!isValidDLLStorageClassForLinkage(DLLStorageClass, Linkage))
5906  return error(LinkageLoc,
5907  "symbol with local linkage cannot have a DLL storage class");
5908 
5909  if (!FunctionType::isValidReturnType(RetType))
5910  return error(RetTypeLoc, "invalid function return type");
5911 
5912  LocTy NameLoc = Lex.getLoc();
5913 
5914  std::string FunctionName;
5915  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::GlobalVar) {
5916  FunctionName = Lex.getStrVal();
5917  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::GlobalID) { // @42 is ok.
5918  unsigned NameID = Lex.getUIntVal();
5919 
5920  if (NameID != NumberedVals.size())
5921  return tokError("function expected to be numbered '%" +
5922  Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
5923  } else {
5924  return tokError("expected function name");
5925  }
5926 
5927  Lex.Lex();
5928 
5929  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::lparen)
5930  return tokError("expected '(' in function argument list");
5931 
5932  SmallVector<ArgInfo, 8> ArgList;
5933  bool IsVarArg;
5934  AttrBuilder FuncAttrs(M->getContext());
5935  std::vector<unsigned> FwdRefAttrGrps;
5936  LocTy BuiltinLoc;
5937  std::string Section;
5938  std::string Partition;
5939  MaybeAlign Alignment;
5940  std::string GC;
5941  GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr UnnamedAddr = GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::None;
5942  unsigned AddrSpace = 0;
5943  Constant *Prefix = nullptr;
5944  Constant *Prologue = nullptr;
5945  Constant *PersonalityFn = nullptr;
5946  Comdat *C;
5947 
5948  if (parseArgumentList(ArgList, IsVarArg) ||
5949  parseOptionalUnnamedAddr(UnnamedAddr) ||
5950  parseOptionalProgramAddrSpace(AddrSpace) ||
5951  parseFnAttributeValuePairs(FuncAttrs, FwdRefAttrGrps, false,
5952  BuiltinLoc) ||
5953  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_section) && parseStringConstant(Section)) ||
5954  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_partition) && parseStringConstant(Partition)) ||
5955  parseOptionalComdat(FunctionName, C) ||
5956  parseOptionalAlignment(Alignment) ||
5957  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_gc) && parseStringConstant(GC)) ||
5958  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_prefix) && parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Prefix)) ||
5959  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_prologue) && parseGlobalTypeAndValue(Prologue)) ||
5960  (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_personality) &&
5961  parseGlobalTypeAndValue(PersonalityFn)))
5962  return true;
5963 
5964  if (FuncAttrs.contains(Attribute::Builtin))
5965  return error(BuiltinLoc, "'builtin' attribute not valid on function");
5966 
5967  // If the alignment was parsed as an attribute, move to the alignment field.
5968  if (MaybeAlign A = FuncAttrs.getAlignment()) {
5969  Alignment = A;
5970  FuncAttrs.removeAttribute(Attribute::Alignment);
5971  }
5972 
5973  // Okay, if we got here, the function is syntactically valid. Convert types
5974  // and do semantic checks.
5975  std::vector<Type*> ParamTypeList;
5976  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> Attrs;
5977 
5978  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
5979  ParamTypeList.push_back(ArgList[i].Ty);
5980  Attrs.push_back(ArgList[i].Attrs);
5981  }
5982 
5983  AttributeList PAL =
5984  AttributeList::get(Context, AttributeSet::get(Context, FuncAttrs),
5985  AttributeSet::get(Context, RetAttrs), Attrs);
5986 
5987  if (PAL.hasParamAttr(0, Attribute::StructRet) && !RetType->isVoidTy())
5988  return error(RetTypeLoc, "functions with 'sret' argument must return void");
5989 
5990  FunctionType *FT = FunctionType::get(RetType, ParamTypeList, IsVarArg);
5991  PointerType *PFT = PointerType::get(FT, AddrSpace);
5992 
5993  Fn = nullptr;
5994  GlobalValue *FwdFn = nullptr;
5995  if (!FunctionName.empty()) {
5996  // If this was a definition of a forward reference, remove the definition
5997  // from the forward reference table and fill in the forward ref.
5998  auto FRVI = ForwardRefVals.find(FunctionName);
5999  if (FRVI != ForwardRefVals.end()) {
6000  FwdFn = FRVI->second.first;
6001  if (!FwdFn->getType()->isOpaque() &&
6002  !FwdFn->getType()->getNonOpaquePointerElementType()->isFunctionTy())
6003  return error(FRVI->second.second, "invalid forward reference to "
6004  "function as global value!");
6005  if (FwdFn->getType() != PFT)
6006  return error(FRVI->second.second,
6007  "invalid forward reference to "
6008  "function '" +
6009  FunctionName +
6010  "' with wrong type: "
6011  "expected '" +
6012  getTypeString(PFT) + "' but was '" +
6013  getTypeString(FwdFn->getType()) + "'");
6014  ForwardRefVals.erase(FRVI);
6015  } else if ((Fn = M->getFunction(FunctionName))) {
6016  // Reject redefinitions.
6017  return error(NameLoc,
6018  "invalid redefinition of function '" + FunctionName + "'");
6019  } else if (M->getNamedValue(FunctionName)) {
6020  return error(NameLoc, "redefinition of function '@" + FunctionName + "'");
6021  }
6022 
6023  } else {
6024  // If this is a definition of a forward referenced function, make sure the
6025  // types agree.
6026  auto I = ForwardRefValIDs.find(NumberedVals.size());
6027  if (I != ForwardRefValIDs.end()) {
6028  FwdFn = I->second.first;
6029  if (FwdFn->getType() != PFT)
6030  return error(NameLoc, "type of definition and forward reference of '@" +
6031  Twine(NumberedVals.size()) +
6032  "' disagree: "
6033  "expected '" +
6034  getTypeString(PFT) + "' but was '" +
6035  getTypeString(FwdFn->getType()) + "'");
6036  ForwardRefValIDs.erase(I);
6037  }
6038  }
6039 
6040  Fn = Function::Create(FT, GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, AddrSpace,
6041  FunctionName, M);
6042 
6043  assert(Fn->getAddressSpace() == AddrSpace && "Created function in wrong AS");
6044 
6045  if (FunctionName.empty())
6046  NumberedVals.push_back(Fn);
6047 
6048  Fn->setLinkage((GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)Linkage);
6049  maybeSetDSOLocal(DSOLocal, *Fn);
6050  Fn->setVisibility((GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes)Visibility);
6051  Fn->setDLLStorageClass((GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes)DLLStorageClass);
6052  Fn->setCallingConv(CC);
6053  Fn->setAttributes(PAL);
6054  Fn->setUnnamedAddr(UnnamedAddr);
6055  if (Alignment)
6056  Fn->setAlignment(*Alignment);
6057  Fn->setSection(Section);
6058  Fn->setPartition(Partition);
6059  Fn->setComdat(C);
6060  Fn->setPersonalityFn(PersonalityFn);
6061  if (!GC.empty()) Fn->setGC(GC);
6062  Fn->setPrefixData(Prefix);
6063  Fn->setPrologueData(Prologue);
6064  ForwardRefAttrGroups[Fn] = FwdRefAttrGrps;
6065 
6066  // Add all of the arguments we parsed to the function.
6067  Function::arg_iterator ArgIt = Fn->arg_begin();
6068  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i, ++ArgIt) {
6069  // If the argument has a name, insert it into the argument symbol table.
6070  if (ArgList[i].Name.empty()) continue;
6071 
6072  // Set the name, if it conflicted, it will be auto-renamed.
6073  ArgIt->setName(ArgList[i].Name);
6074 
6075  if (ArgIt->getName() != ArgList[i].Name)
6076  return error(ArgList[i].Loc,
6077  "redefinition of argument '%" + ArgList[i].Name + "'");
6078  }
6079 
6080  if (FwdFn) {
6081  FwdFn->replaceAllUsesWith(Fn);
6082  FwdFn->eraseFromParent();
6083  }
6084 
6085  if (IsDefine)
6086  return false;
6087 
6088  // Check the declaration has no block address forward references.
6089  ValID ID;
6090  if (FunctionName.empty()) {
6091  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalID;
6092  ID.UIntVal = NumberedVals.size() - 1;
6093  } else {
6094  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalName;
6095  ID.StrVal = FunctionName;
6096  }
6097  auto Blocks = ForwardRefBlockAddresses.find(ID);
6098  if (Blocks != ForwardRefBlockAddresses.end())
6099  return error(Blocks->first.Loc,
6100  "cannot take blockaddress inside a declaration");
6101  return false;
6102 }
6103 
6104 bool LLParser::PerFunctionState::resolveForwardRefBlockAddresses() {
6105  ValID ID;
6106  if (FunctionNumber == -1) {
6107  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalName;
6108  ID.StrVal = std::string(F.getName());
6109  } else {
6110  ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalID;
6111  ID.UIntVal = FunctionNumber;
6112  }
6113 
6114  auto Blocks = P.ForwardRefBlockAddresses.find(ID);
6115  if (Blocks == P.ForwardRefBlockAddresses.end())
6116  return false;
6117 
6118  for (const auto &I : Blocks->second) {
6119  const ValID &BBID = I.first;
6120  GlobalValue *GV = I.second;
6121 
6122  assert((BBID.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID || BBID.Kind == ValID::t_LocalName) &&
6123  "Expected local id or name");
6124  BasicBlock *BB;
6125  if (BBID.Kind == ValID::t_LocalName)
6126  BB = getBB(BBID.StrVal, BBID.Loc);
6127  else
6128  BB = getBB(BBID.UIntVal, BBID.Loc);
6129  if (!BB)
6130  return P.error(BBID.Loc, "referenced value is not a basic block");
6131 
6132  Value *ResolvedVal = BlockAddress::get(&F, BB);
6133  ResolvedVal = P.checkValidVariableType(BBID.Loc, BBID.StrVal, GV->getType(),
6134  ResolvedVal);
6135  if (!ResolvedVal)
6136  return true;
6137  GV->replaceAllUsesWith(ResolvedVal);
6138  GV->eraseFromParent();
6139  }
6140 
6141  P.ForwardRefBlockAddresses.erase(Blocks);
6142  return false;
6143 }
6144 
6145 /// parseFunctionBody
6146 /// ::= '{' BasicBlock+ UseListOrderDirective* '}'
6147 bool LLParser::parseFunctionBody(Function &Fn) {
6148  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::lbrace)
6149  return tokError("expected '{' in function body");
6150  Lex.Lex(); // eat the {.
6151 
6152  int FunctionNumber = -1;
6153  if (!Fn.hasName()) FunctionNumber = NumberedVals.size()-1;
6154 
6155  PerFunctionState PFS(*this, Fn, FunctionNumber);
6156 
6157  // Resolve block addresses and allow basic blocks to be forward-declared
6158  // within this function.
6159  if (PFS.resolveForwardRefBlockAddresses())
6160  return true;
6161  SaveAndRestore ScopeExit(BlockAddressPFS, &PFS);
6162 
6163  // We need at least one basic block.
6164  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rbrace || Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_uselistorder)
6165  return tokError("function body requires at least one basic block");
6166 
6167  while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rbrace &&
6168  Lex.getKind() != lltok::kw_uselistorder)
6169  if (parseBasicBlock(PFS))
6170  return true;
6171 
6172  while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rbrace)
6173  if (parseUseListOrder(&PFS))
6174  return true;
6175 
6176  // Eat the }.
6177  Lex.Lex();
6178 
6179  // Verify function is ok.
6180  return PFS.finishFunction();
6181 }
6182 
6183 /// parseBasicBlock
6184 /// ::= (LabelStr|LabelID)? Instruction*
6185 bool LLParser::parseBasicBlock(PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6186  // If this basic block starts out with a name, remember it.
6187  std::string Name;
6188  int NameID = -1;
6189  LocTy NameLoc = Lex.getLoc();
6190  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LabelStr) {
6191  Name = Lex.getStrVal();
6192  Lex.Lex();
6193  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LabelID) {
6194  NameID = Lex.getUIntVal();
6195  Lex.Lex();
6196  }
6197 
6198  BasicBlock *BB = PFS.defineBB(Name, NameID, NameLoc);
6199  if (!BB)
6200  return true;
6201 
6202  std::string NameStr;
6203 
6204  // parse the instructions in this block until we get a terminator.
6205  Instruction *Inst;
6206  do {
6207  // This instruction may have three possibilities for a name: a) none
6208  // specified, b) name specified "%foo =", c) number specified: "%4 =".
6209  LocTy NameLoc = Lex.getLoc();
6210  int NameID = -1;
6211  NameStr = "";
6212 
6213  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVarID) {
6214  NameID = Lex.getUIntVal();
6215  Lex.Lex();
6216  if (parseToken(lltok::equal, "expected '=' after instruction id"))
6217  return true;
6218  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVar) {
6219  NameStr = Lex.getStrVal();
6220  Lex.Lex();
6221  if (parseToken(lltok::equal, "expected '=' after instruction name"))
6222  return true;
6223  }
6224 
6225  switch (parseInstruction(Inst, BB, PFS)) {
6226  default:
6227  llvm_unreachable("Unknown parseInstruction result!");
6228  case InstError: return true;
6229  case InstNormal:
6230  Inst->insertInto(BB, BB->end());
6231 
6232  // With a normal result, we check to see if the instruction is followed by
6233  // a comma and metadata.
6234  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma))
6235  if (parseInstructionMetadata(*Inst))
6236  return true;
6237  break;
6238  case InstExtraComma:
6239  Inst->insertInto(BB, BB->end());
6240 
6241  // If the instruction parser ate an extra comma at the end of it, it
6242  // *must* be followed by metadata.
6243  if (parseInstructionMetadata(*Inst))
6244  return true;
6245  break;
6246  }
6247 
6248  // Set the name on the instruction.
6249  if (PFS.setInstName(NameID, NameStr, NameLoc, Inst))
6250  return true;
6251  } while (!Inst->isTerminator());
6252 
6253  return false;
6254 }

6257 // Instruction Parsing.

6260 /// parseInstruction - parse one of the many different instructions.
6261 ///
6262 int LLParser::parseInstruction(Instruction *&Inst, BasicBlock *BB,
6263  PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6264  lltok::Kind Token = Lex.getKind();
6265  if (Token == lltok::Eof)
6266  return tokError("found end of file when expecting more instructions");
6267  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
6268  unsigned KeywordVal = Lex.getUIntVal();
6269  Lex.Lex(); // Eat the keyword.
6270 
6271  switch (Token) {
6272  default:
6273  return error(Loc, "expected instruction opcode");
6274  // Terminator Instructions.
6275  case lltok::kw_unreachable: Inst = new UnreachableInst(Context); return false;
6276  case lltok::kw_ret:
6277  return parseRet(Inst, BB, PFS);
6278  case lltok::kw_br:
6279  return parseBr(Inst, PFS);
6280  case lltok::kw_switch:
6281  return parseSwitch(Inst, PFS);
6282  case lltok::kw_indirectbr:
6283  return parseIndirectBr(Inst, PFS);
6284  case lltok::kw_invoke:
6285  return parseInvoke(Inst, PFS);
6286  case lltok::kw_resume:
6287  return parseResume(Inst, PFS);
6288  case lltok::kw_cleanupret:
6289  return parseCleanupRet(Inst, PFS);
6290  case lltok::kw_catchret:
6291  return parseCatchRet(Inst, PFS);
6292  case lltok::kw_catchswitch:
6293  return parseCatchSwitch(Inst, PFS);
6294  case lltok::kw_catchpad:
6295  return parseCatchPad(Inst, PFS);
6296  case lltok::kw_cleanuppad:
6297  return parseCleanupPad(Inst, PFS);
6298  case lltok::kw_callbr:
6299  return parseCallBr(Inst, PFS);
6300  // Unary Operators.
6301  case lltok::kw_fneg: {
6302  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
6303  int Res = parseUnaryOp(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal, /*IsFP*/ true);
6304  if (Res != 0)
6305  return Res;
6306  if (FMF.any())
6307  Inst->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
6308  return false;
6309  }
6310  // Binary Operators.
6311  case lltok::kw_add:
6312  case lltok::kw_sub:
6313  case lltok::kw_mul:
6314  case lltok::kw_shl: {
6315  bool NUW = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw);
6316  bool NSW = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nsw);
6317  if (!NUW) NUW = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw);
6318 
6319  if (parseArithmetic(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal, /*IsFP*/ false))
6320  return true;
6321 
6322  if (NUW) cast<BinaryOperator>(Inst)->setHasNoUnsignedWrap(true);
6323  if (NSW) cast<BinaryOperator>(Inst)->setHasNoSignedWrap(true);
6324  return false;
6325  }
6326  case lltok::kw_fadd:
6327  case lltok::kw_fsub:
6328  case lltok::kw_fmul:
6329  case lltok::kw_fdiv:
6330  case lltok::kw_frem: {
6331  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
6332  int Res = parseArithmetic(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal, /*IsFP*/ true);
6333  if (Res != 0)
6334  return Res;
6335  if (FMF.any())
6336  Inst->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
6337  return 0;
6338  }
6339 
6340  case lltok::kw_sdiv:
6341  case lltok::kw_udiv:
6342  case lltok::kw_lshr:
6343  case lltok::kw_ashr: {
6344  bool Exact = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_exact);
6345 
6346  if (parseArithmetic(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal, /*IsFP*/ false))
6347  return true;
6348  if (Exact) cast<BinaryOperator>(Inst)->setIsExact(true);
6349  return false;
6350  }
6351 
6352  case lltok::kw_urem:
6353  case lltok::kw_srem:
6354  return parseArithmetic(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal,
6355  /*IsFP*/ false);
6356  case lltok::kw_and:
6357  case lltok::kw_or:
6358  case lltok::kw_xor:
6359  return parseLogical(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal);
6360  case lltok::kw_icmp:
6361  return parseCompare(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal);
6362  case lltok::kw_fcmp: {
6363  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
6364  int Res = parseCompare(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal);
6365  if (Res != 0)
6366  return Res;
6367  if (FMF.any())
6368  Inst->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
6369  return 0;
6370  }
6371 
6372  // Casts.
6373  case lltok::kw_trunc:
6374  case lltok::kw_zext:
6375  case lltok::kw_sext:
6376  case lltok::kw_fptrunc:
6377  case lltok::kw_fpext:
6378  case lltok::kw_bitcast:
6379  case lltok::kw_addrspacecast:
6380  case lltok::kw_uitofp:
6381  case lltok::kw_sitofp:
6382  case lltok::kw_fptoui:
6383  case lltok::kw_fptosi:
6384  case lltok::kw_inttoptr:
6385  case lltok::kw_ptrtoint:
6386  return parseCast(Inst, PFS, KeywordVal);
6387  // Other.
6388  case lltok::kw_select: {
6389  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
6390  int Res = parseSelect(Inst, PFS);
6391  if (Res != 0)
6392  return Res;
6393  if (FMF.any()) {
6394  if (!isa<FPMathOperator>(Inst))
6395  return error(Loc, "fast-math-flags specified for select without "
6396  "floating-point scalar or vector return type");
6397  Inst->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
6398  }
6399  return 0;
6400  }
6401  case lltok::kw_va_arg:
6402  return parseVAArg(Inst, PFS);
6403  case lltok::kw_extractelement:
6404  return parseExtractElement(Inst, PFS);
6405  case lltok::kw_insertelement:
6406  return parseInsertElement(Inst, PFS);
6407  case lltok::kw_shufflevector:
6408  return parseShuffleVector(Inst, PFS);
6409  case lltok::kw_phi: {
6410  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
6411  int Res = parsePHI(Inst, PFS);
6412  if (Res != 0)
6413  return Res;
6414  if (FMF.any()) {
6415  if (!isa<FPMathOperator>(Inst))
6416  return error(Loc, "fast-math-flags specified for phi without "
6417  "floating-point scalar or vector return type");
6418  Inst->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
6419  }
6420  return 0;
6421  }
6422  case lltok::kw_landingpad:
6423  return parseLandingPad(Inst, PFS);
6424  case lltok::kw_freeze:
6425  return parseFreeze(Inst, PFS);
6426  // Call.
6427  case lltok::kw_call:
6428  return parseCall(Inst, PFS, CallInst::TCK_None);
6429  case lltok::kw_tail:
6430  return parseCall(Inst, PFS, CallInst::TCK_Tail);
6431  case lltok::kw_musttail:
6432  return parseCall(Inst, PFS, CallInst::TCK_MustTail);
6433  case lltok::kw_notail:
6434  return parseCall(Inst, PFS, CallInst::TCK_NoTail);
6435  // Memory.
6436  case lltok::kw_alloca:
6437  return parseAlloc(Inst, PFS);
6438  case lltok::kw_load:
6439  return parseLoad(Inst, PFS);
6440  case lltok::kw_store:
6441  return parseStore(Inst, PFS);
6442  case lltok::kw_cmpxchg:
6443  return parseCmpXchg(Inst, PFS);
6444  case lltok::kw_atomicrmw:
6445  return parseAtomicRMW(Inst, PFS);
6446  case lltok::kw_fence:
6447  return parseFence(Inst, PFS);
6448  case lltok::kw_getelementptr:
6449  return parseGetElementPtr(Inst, PFS);
6450  case lltok::kw_extractvalue:
6451  return parseExtractValue(Inst, PFS);
6452  case lltok::kw_insertvalue:
6453  return parseInsertValue(Inst, PFS);
6454  }
6455 }

6457 /// parseCmpPredicate - parse an integer or fp predicate, based on Kind.
6458 bool LLParser::parseCmpPredicate(unsigned &P, unsigned Opc) {
6459  if (Opc == Instruction::FCmp) {
6460  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
6461  default:
6462  return tokError("expected fcmp predicate (e.g. 'oeq')");
6463  case lltok::kw_oeq: P = CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ; break;
6464  case lltok::kw_one: P = CmpInst::FCMP_ONE; break;
6465  case lltok::kw_olt: P = CmpInst::FCMP_OLT; break;
6466  case lltok::kw_ogt: P = CmpInst::FCMP_OGT; break;
6467  case lltok::kw_ole: P = CmpInst::FCMP_OLE; break;
6468  case lltok::kw_oge: P = CmpInst::FCMP_OGE; break;
6469  case lltok::kw_ord: P = CmpInst::FCMP_ORD; break;
6470  case lltok::kw_uno: P = CmpInst::FCMP_UNO; break;
6471  case lltok::kw_ueq: P = CmpInst::FCMP_UEQ; break;
6472  case lltok::kw_une: P = CmpInst::FCMP_UNE; break;
6473  case lltok::kw_ult: P = CmpInst::FCMP_ULT; break;
6474  case lltok::kw_ugt: P = CmpInst::FCMP_UGT; break;
6475  case lltok::kw_ule: P = CmpInst::FCMP_ULE; break;
6476  case lltok::kw_uge: P = CmpInst::FCMP_UGE; break;
6477  case lltok::kw_true: P = CmpInst::FCMP_TRUE; break;
6478  case lltok::kw_false: P = CmpInst::FCMP_FALSE; break;
6479  }
6480  } else {
6481  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
6482  default:
6483  return tokError("expected icmp predicate (e.g. 'eq')");
6484  case lltok::kw_eq: P = CmpInst::ICMP_EQ; break;
6485  case lltok::kw_ne: P = CmpInst::ICMP_NE; break;
6486  case lltok::kw_slt: P = CmpInst::ICMP_SLT; break;
6487  case lltok::kw_sgt: P = CmpInst::ICMP_SGT; break;
6488  case lltok::kw_sle: P = CmpInst::ICMP_SLE; break;
6489  case lltok::kw_sge: P = CmpInst::ICMP_SGE; break;
6490  case lltok::kw_ult: P = CmpInst::ICMP_ULT; break;
6491  case lltok::kw_ugt: P = CmpInst::ICMP_UGT; break;
6492  case lltok::kw_ule: P = CmpInst::ICMP_ULE; break;
6493  case lltok::kw_uge: P = CmpInst::ICMP_UGE; break;
6494  }
6495  }
6496  Lex.Lex();
6497  return false;
6498 }

6504 /// parseRet - parse a return instruction.
6505 /// ::= 'ret' void (',' !dbg, !1)*
6506 /// ::= 'ret' TypeAndValue (',' !dbg, !1)*
6507 bool LLParser::parseRet(Instruction *&Inst, BasicBlock *BB,
6508  PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6509  SMLoc TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
6510  Type *Ty = nullptr;
6511  if (parseType(Ty, true /*void allowed*/))
6512  return true;
6513 
6514  Type *ResType = PFS.getFunction().getReturnType();
6515 
6516  if (Ty->isVoidTy()) {
6517  if (!ResType->isVoidTy())
6518  return error(TypeLoc, "value doesn't match function result type '" +
6519  getTypeString(ResType) + "'");
6520 
6521  Inst = ReturnInst::Create(Context);
6522  return false;
6523  }
6524 
6525  Value *RV;
6526  if (parseValue(Ty, RV, PFS))
6527  return true;
6528 
6529  if (ResType != RV->getType())
6530  return error(TypeLoc, "value doesn't match function result type '" +
6531  getTypeString(ResType) + "'");
6532 
6533  Inst = ReturnInst::Create(Context, RV);
6534  return false;
6535 }
6536 
6537 /// parseBr
6538 /// ::= 'br' TypeAndValue
6539 /// ::= 'br' TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue
6540 bool LLParser::parseBr(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6541  LocTy Loc, Loc2;
6542  Value *Op0;
6543  BasicBlock *Op1, *Op2;
6544  if (parseTypeAndValue(Op0, Loc, PFS))
6545  return true;
6546 
6547  if (BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(Op0)) {
6548  Inst = BranchInst::Create(BB);
6549  return false;
6550  }
6551 
6552  if (Op0->getType() != Type::getInt1Ty(Context))
6553  return error(Loc, "branch condition must have 'i1' type");
6554 
6555  if (parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after branch condition") ||
6556  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(Op1, Loc, PFS) ||
6557  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after true destination") ||
6558  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(Op2, Loc2, PFS))
6559  return true;
6560 
6561  Inst = BranchInst::Create(Op1, Op2, Op0);
6562  return false;
6563 }
6564 
6565 /// parseSwitch
6566 /// Instruction
6567 /// ::= 'switch' TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue '[' JumpTable ']'
6568 /// JumpTable
6569 /// ::= (TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue)*
6570 bool LLParser::parseSwitch(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6571  LocTy CondLoc, BBLoc;
6572  Value *Cond;
6573  BasicBlock *DefaultBB;
6574  if (parseTypeAndValue(Cond, CondLoc, PFS) ||
6575  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after switch condition") ||
6576  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DefaultBB, BBLoc, PFS) ||
6577  parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' with switch table"))
6578  return true;
6579 
6580  if (!Cond->getType()->isIntegerTy())
6581  return error(CondLoc, "switch condition must have integer type");
6582 
6583  // parse the jump table pairs.
6584  SmallPtrSet<Value*, 32> SeenCases;
6585  SmallVector<std::pair<ConstantInt*, BasicBlock*>, 32> Table;
6586  while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rsquare) {
6587  Value *Constant;
6588  BasicBlock *DestBB;
6589 
6590  if (parseTypeAndValue(Constant, CondLoc, PFS) ||
6591  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after case value") ||
6592  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
6593  return true;
6594 
6595  if (!SeenCases.insert(Constant).second)
6596  return error(CondLoc, "duplicate case value in switch");
6597  if (!isa<ConstantInt>(Constant))
6598  return error(CondLoc, "case value is not a constant integer");
6599 
6600  Table.push_back(std::make_pair(cast<ConstantInt>(Constant), DestBB));
6601  }
6602 
6603  Lex.Lex(); // Eat the ']'.
6604 
6605  SwitchInst *SI = SwitchInst::Create(Cond, DefaultBB, Table.size());
6606  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Table.size(); i != e; ++i)
6607  SI->addCase(Table[i].first, Table[i].second);
6608  Inst = SI;
6609  return false;
6610 }
6611 
6612 /// parseIndirectBr
6613 /// Instruction
6614 /// ::= 'indirectbr' TypeAndValue ',' '[' LabelList ']'
6615 bool LLParser::parseIndirectBr(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6616  LocTy AddrLoc;
6617  Value *Address;
6618  if (parseTypeAndValue(Address, AddrLoc, PFS) ||
6619  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after indirectbr address") ||
6620  parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' with indirectbr"))
6621  return true;
6622 
6623  if (!Address->getType()->isPointerTy())
6624  return error(AddrLoc, "indirectbr address must have pointer type");
6625 
6626  // parse the destination list.
6627  SmallVector<BasicBlock*, 16> DestList;
6628 
6629  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rsquare) {
6630  BasicBlock *DestBB;
6631  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
6632  return true;
6633  DestList.push_back(DestBB);
6634 
6635  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
6636  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
6637  return true;
6638  DestList.push_back(DestBB);
6639  }
6640  }
6641 
6642  if (parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected ']' at end of block list"))
6643  return true;
6644 
6645  IndirectBrInst *IBI = IndirectBrInst::Create(Address, DestList.size());
6646  for (unsigned i = 0, e = DestList.size(); i != e; ++i)
6647  IBI->addDestination(DestList[i]);
6648  Inst = IBI;
6649  return false;
6650 }
6651 
6652 // If RetType is a non-function pointer type, then this is the short syntax
6653 // for the call, which means that RetType is just the return type. Infer the
6654 // rest of the function argument types from the arguments that are present.
6655 bool LLParser::resolveFunctionType(Type *RetType,
6656  const SmallVector<ParamInfo, 16> &ArgList,
6657  FunctionType *&FuncTy) {
6658  FuncTy = dyn_cast<FunctionType>(RetType);
6659  if (!FuncTy) {
6660  // Pull out the types of all of the arguments...
6661  std::vector<Type*> ParamTypes;
6662  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i)
6663  ParamTypes.push_back(ArgList[i].V->getType());
6664 
6665  if (!FunctionType::isValidReturnType(RetType))
6666  return true;
6667 
6668  FuncTy = FunctionType::get(RetType, ParamTypes, false);
6669  }
6670  return false;
6671 }

6673 /// parseInvoke
6674 /// ::= 'invoke' OptionalCallingConv OptionalAttrs Type Value ParamList
6675 /// OptionalAttrs 'to' TypeAndValue 'unwind' TypeAndValue
6676 bool LLParser::parseInvoke(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6677  LocTy CallLoc = Lex.getLoc();
6678  AttrBuilder RetAttrs(M->getContext()), FnAttrs(M->getContext());
6679  std::vector<unsigned> FwdRefAttrGrps;
6680  LocTy NoBuiltinLoc;
6681  unsigned CC;
6682  unsigned InvokeAddrSpace;
6683  Type *RetType = nullptr;
6684  LocTy RetTypeLoc;
6685  ValID CalleeID;
6686  SmallVector<ParamInfo, 16> ArgList;
6687  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> BundleList;
6688 
6689  BasicBlock *NormalBB, *UnwindBB;
6690  if (parseOptionalCallingConv(CC) || parseOptionalReturnAttrs(RetAttrs) ||
6691  parseOptionalProgramAddrSpace(InvokeAddrSpace) ||
6692  parseType(RetType, RetTypeLoc, true /*void allowed*/) ||
6693  parseValID(CalleeID, &PFS) || parseParameterList(ArgList, PFS) ||
6694  parseFnAttributeValuePairs(FnAttrs, FwdRefAttrGrps, false,
6695  NoBuiltinLoc) ||
6696  parseOptionalOperandBundles(BundleList, PFS) ||
6697  parseToken(lltok::kw_to, "expected 'to' in invoke") ||
6698  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(NormalBB, PFS) ||
6699  parseToken(lltok::kw_unwind, "expected 'unwind' in invoke") ||
6700  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(UnwindBB, PFS))
6701  return true;
6702 
6703  // If RetType is a non-function pointer type, then this is the short syntax
6704  // for the call, which means that RetType is just the return type. Infer the
6705  // rest of the function argument types from the arguments that are present.
6706  FunctionType *Ty;
6707  if (resolveFunctionType(RetType, ArgList, Ty))
6708  return error(RetTypeLoc, "Invalid result type for LLVM function");
6709 
6710  CalleeID.FTy = Ty;
6711 
6712  // Look up the callee.
6713  Value *Callee;
6714  if (convertValIDToValue(PointerType::get(Ty, InvokeAddrSpace), CalleeID,
6715  Callee, &PFS))
6716  return true;
6717 
6718  // Set up the Attribute for the function.
6719  SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args;
6720  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> ArgAttrs;
6721 
6722  // Loop through FunctionType's arguments and ensure they are specified
6723  // correctly. Also, gather any parameter attributes.
6724  FunctionType::param_iterator I = Ty->param_begin();
6725  FunctionType::param_iterator E = Ty->param_end();
6726  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
6727  Type *ExpectedTy = nullptr;
6728  if (I != E) {
6729  ExpectedTy = *I++;
6730  } else if (!Ty->isVarArg()) {
6731  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "too many arguments specified");
6732  }
6733 
6734  if (ExpectedTy && ExpectedTy != ArgList[i].V->getType())
6735  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "argument is not of expected type '" +
6736  getTypeString(ExpectedTy) + "'");
6737  Args.push_back(ArgList[i].V);
6738  ArgAttrs.push_back(ArgList[i].Attrs);
6739  }
6740 
6741  if (I != E)
6742  return error(CallLoc, "not enough parameters specified for call");
6743 
6744  // Finish off the Attribute and check them
6745  AttributeList PAL =
6746  AttributeList::get(Context, AttributeSet::get(Context, FnAttrs),
6747  AttributeSet::get(Context, RetAttrs), ArgAttrs);
6748 
6749  InvokeInst *II =
6750  InvokeInst::Create(Ty, Callee, NormalBB, UnwindBB, Args, BundleList);
6751  II->setCallingConv(CC);
6752  II->setAttributes(PAL);
6753  ForwardRefAttrGroups[II] = FwdRefAttrGrps;
6754  Inst = II;
6755  return false;
6756 }

6758 /// parseResume
6759 /// ::= 'resume' TypeAndValue
6760 bool LLParser::parseResume(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6761  Value *Exn; LocTy ExnLoc;
6762  if (parseTypeAndValue(Exn, ExnLoc, PFS))
6763  return true;
6764 
6765  ResumeInst *RI = ResumeInst::Create(Exn);
6766  Inst = RI;
6767  return false;
6768 }

6770 bool LLParser::parseExceptionArgs(SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Args,
6771  PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6772  if (parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' in catchpad/cleanuppad"))
6773  return true;
6774 
6775  while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rsquare) {
6776  // If this isn't the first argument, we need a comma.
6777  if (!Args.empty() &&
6778  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' in argument list"))
6779  return true;
6780 
6781  // parse the argument.
6782  LocTy ArgLoc;
6783  Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
6784  if (parseType(ArgTy, ArgLoc))
6785  return true;
6786 
6787  Value *V;
6788  if (ArgTy->isMetadataTy()) {
6789  if (parseMetadataAsValue(V, PFS))
6790  return true;
6791  } else {
6792  if (parseValue(ArgTy, V, PFS))
6793  return true;
6794  }
6795  Args.push_back(V);
6796  }
6797 
6798  Lex.Lex(); // Lex the ']'.
6799  return false;
6800 }

6802 /// parseCleanupRet
6803 /// ::= 'cleanupret' from Value unwind ('to' 'caller' | TypeAndValue)
6804 bool LLParser::parseCleanupRet(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6805  Value *CleanupPad = nullptr;
6806 
6807  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_from, "expected 'from' after cleanupret"))
6808  return true;
6809 
6810  if (parseValue(Type::getTokenTy(Context), CleanupPad, PFS))
6811  return true;
6812 
6813  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_unwind, "expected 'unwind' in cleanupret"))
6814  return true;
6815 
6816  BasicBlock *UnwindBB = nullptr;
6817  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_to) {
6818  Lex.Lex();
6819  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_caller, "expected 'caller' in cleanupret"))
6820  return true;
6821  } else {
6822  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(UnwindBB, PFS)) {
6823  return true;
6824  }
6825  }
6826 
6827  Inst = CleanupReturnInst::Create(CleanupPad, UnwindBB);
6828  return false;
6829 }

6851 /// parseCatchSwitch
6852 /// ::= 'catchswitch' within Parent
6853 bool LLParser::parseCatchSwitch(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6854  Value *ParentPad;
6855 
6856  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_within, "expected 'within' after catchswitch"))
6857  return true;
6858 
6859  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::kw_none && Lex.getKind() != lltok::LocalVar &&
6860  Lex.getKind() != lltok::LocalVarID)
6861  return tokError("expected scope value for catchswitch");
6862 
6863  if (parseValue(Type::getTokenTy(Context), ParentPad, PFS))
6864  return true;
6865 
6866  if (parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' with catchswitch labels"))
6867  return true;
6868 
6869  SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 32> Table;
6870  do {
6871  BasicBlock *DestBB;
6872  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
6873  return true;
6874  Table.push_back(DestBB);
6875  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
6876 
6877  if (parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected ']' after catchswitch labels"))
6878  return true;
6879 
6880  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_unwind, "expected 'unwind' after catchswitch scope"))
6881  return true;
6882 
6883  BasicBlock *UnwindBB = nullptr;
6884  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_to)) {
6885  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_caller, "expected 'caller' in catchswitch"))
6886  return true;
6887  } else {
6888  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(UnwindBB, PFS))
6889  return true;
6890  }
6891 
6892  auto *CatchSwitch =
6893  CatchSwitchInst::Create(ParentPad, UnwindBB, Table.size());
6894  for (BasicBlock *DestBB : Table)
6895  CatchSwitch->addHandler(DestBB);
6896  Inst = CatchSwitch;
6897  return false;
6898 }

6949 /// parseUnaryOp
6950 /// ::= UnaryOp TypeAndValue ',' Value
6951 ///
6952 /// If IsFP is false, then any integer operand is allowed, if it is true, any fp
6953 /// operand is allowed.
6954 bool LLParser::parseUnaryOp(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS,
6955  unsigned Opc, bool IsFP) {

6958  return true;

6961  : LHS->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy();

6970 /// parseCallBr
6971 /// ::= 'callbr' OptionalCallingConv OptionalAttrs Type Value ParamList
6972 /// OptionalAttrs OptionalOperandBundles 'to' TypeAndValue
6973 /// '[' LabelList ']'
6974 bool LLParser::parseCallBr(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
6975  LocTy CallLoc = Lex.getLoc();
6976  AttrBuilder RetAttrs(M->getContext()), FnAttrs(M->getContext());
6977  std::vector<unsigned> FwdRefAttrGrps;
6978  LocTy NoBuiltinLoc;
6979  unsigned CC;
6980  Type *RetType = nullptr;
6981  LocTy RetTypeLoc;
6982  ValID CalleeID;
6983  SmallVector<ParamInfo, 16> ArgList;
6984  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> BundleList;
6985 
6986  BasicBlock *DefaultDest;
6987  if (parseOptionalCallingConv(CC) || parseOptionalReturnAttrs(RetAttrs) ||
6988  parseType(RetType, RetTypeLoc, true /*void allowed*/) ||
6989  parseValID(CalleeID, &PFS) || parseParameterList(ArgList, PFS) ||
6990  parseFnAttributeValuePairs(FnAttrs, FwdRefAttrGrps, false,
6991  NoBuiltinLoc) ||
6992  parseOptionalOperandBundles(BundleList, PFS) ||
6993  parseToken(lltok::kw_to, "expected 'to' in callbr") ||
6994  parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DefaultDest, PFS) ||
6995  parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' in callbr"))
6996  return true;
6997 
6998  // parse the destination list.
6999  SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 16> IndirectDests;
7000 
7001  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rsquare) {
7002  BasicBlock *DestBB;
7003  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
7004  return true;
7005  IndirectDests.push_back(DestBB);
7006 
7007  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7008  if (parseTypeAndBasicBlock(DestBB, PFS))
7009  return true;
7010  IndirectDests.push_back(DestBB);
7011  }
7012  }
7013 
7014  if (parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected ']' at end of block list"))
7015  return true;
7016 
7017  // If RetType is a non-function pointer type, then this is the short syntax
7018  // for the call, which means that RetType is just the return type. Infer the
7019  // rest of the function argument types from the arguments that are present.
7020  FunctionType *Ty;
7021  if (resolveFunctionType(RetType, ArgList, Ty))
7022  return error(RetTypeLoc, "Invalid result type for LLVM function");
7023 
7024  CalleeID.FTy = Ty;
7025 
7026  // Look up the callee.
7027  Value *Callee;
7028  if (convertValIDToValue(PointerType::getUnqual(Ty), CalleeID, Callee, &PFS))
7029  return true;
7030 
7031  // Set up the Attribute for the function.
7032  SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args;
7033  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> ArgAttrs;
7034 
7035  // Loop through FunctionType's arguments and ensure they are specified
7036  // correctly. Also, gather any parameter attributes.
7037  FunctionType::param_iterator I = Ty->param_begin();
7038  FunctionType::param_iterator E = Ty->param_end();
7039  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7040  Type *ExpectedTy = nullptr;
7041  if (I != E) {
7042  ExpectedTy = *I++;
7043  } else if (!Ty->isVarArg()) {
7044  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "too many arguments specified");
7045  }
7046 
7047  if (ExpectedTy && ExpectedTy != ArgList[i].V->getType())
7048  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "argument is not of expected type '" +
7049  getTypeString(ExpectedTy) + "'");
7050  Args.push_back(ArgList[i].V);
7051  ArgAttrs.push_back(ArgList[i].Attrs);
7052  }
7053 
7054  if (I != E)
7055  return error(CallLoc, "not enough parameters specified for call");
7056 
7057  // Finish off the Attribute and check them
7058  AttributeList PAL =
7059  AttributeList::get(Context, AttributeSet::get(Context, FnAttrs),
7060  AttributeSet::get(Context, RetAttrs), ArgAttrs);
7061 
7062  CallBrInst *CBI =
7063  CallBrInst::Create(Ty, Callee, DefaultDest, IndirectDests, Args,
7064  BundleList);
7065  CBI->setCallingConv(CC);
7066  CBI->setAttributes(PAL);
7067  ForwardRefAttrGroups[CBI] = FwdRefAttrGrps;
7068  Inst = CBI;
7069  return false;
7070 }

7117 /// parseCompare
7118 /// ::= 'icmp' IPredicates TypeAndValue ',' Value
7119 /// ::= 'fcmp' FPredicates TypeAndValue ',' Value
7120 bool LLParser::parseCompare(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS,
7121  unsigned Opc) {
7122  // parse the integer/fp comparison predicate.
7123  LocTy Loc;
7124  unsigned Pred;
7125  Value *LHS, *RHS;
7126  if (parseCmpPredicate(Pred, Opc) || parseTypeAndValue(LHS, Loc, PFS) ||
7127  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after compare value") ||
7128  parseValue(LHS->getType(), RHS, PFS))
7129  return true;
7130 
7131  if (Opc == Instruction::FCmp) {
7132  if (!LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
7133  return error(Loc, "fcmp requires floating point operands");
7134  Inst = new FCmpInst(CmpInst::Predicate(Pred), LHS, RHS);
7135  } else {
7136  assert(Opc == Instruction::ICmp && "Unknown opcode for CmpInst!");
7137  if (!LHS->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() &&
7138  !LHS->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
7139  return error(Loc, "icmp requires integer operands");
7140  Inst = new ICmpInst(CmpInst::Predicate(Pred), LHS, RHS);
7141  }
7142  return false;
7143 }

7149 /// parseCast
7150 /// ::= CastOpc TypeAndValue 'to' Type
7151 bool LLParser::parseCast(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS,
7152  unsigned Opc) {
7153  LocTy Loc;
7154  Value *Op;
7155  Type *DestTy = nullptr;
7156  if (parseTypeAndValue(Op, Loc, PFS) ||
7157  parseToken(lltok::kw_to, "expected 'to' after cast value") ||
7158  parseType(DestTy))
7159  return true;
7160 
7161  if (!CastInst::castIsValid((Instruction::CastOps)Opc, Op, DestTy)) {
7162  CastInst::castIsValid((Instruction::CastOps)Opc, Op, DestTy);
7163  return error(Loc, "invalid cast opcode for cast from '" +
7164  getTypeString(Op->getType()) + "' to '" +
7165  getTypeString(DestTy) + "'");
7166  }
7167  Inst = CastInst::Create((Instruction::CastOps)Opc, Op, DestTy);
7168  return false;
7169 }

7177  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after select condition") ||
7178  parseTypeAndValue(Op1, PFS) ||
7179  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after select value") ||
7180  parseTypeAndValue(Op2, PFS))
7181  return true;
7182 
7183  if (const char *Reason = SelectInst::areInvalidOperands(Op0, Op1, Op2))
7184  return error(Loc, Reason);
7185 
7186  Inst = SelectInst::Create(Op0, Op1, Op2);
7187  return false;

7263 /// parsePHI
7264 /// ::= 'phi' Type '[' Value ',' Value ']' (',' '[' Value ',' Value ']')*
7265 int LLParser::parsePHI(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7266  Type *Ty = nullptr; LocTy TypeLoc;
7267  Value *Op0, *Op1;
7268 
7269  if (parseType(Ty, TypeLoc))
7270  return true;
7271 
7272  if (!Ty->isFirstClassType())
7273  return error(TypeLoc, "phi node must have first class type");
7274 
7275  bool First = true;
7276  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7277  SmallVector<std::pair<Value*, BasicBlock*>, 16> PHIVals;
7278 
7279  while (true) {
7280  if (First) {
7281  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::lsquare)
7282  break;
7283  First = false;
7284  } else if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::comma))
7285  break;
7286 
7287  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
7288  AteExtraComma = true;
7289  break;
7290  }
7291 
7292  if (parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' in phi value list") ||
7293  parseValue(Ty, Op0, PFS) ||
7294  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after insertelement value") ||
7295  parseValue(Type::getLabelTy(Context), Op1, PFS) ||
7296  parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected ']' in phi value list"))
7297  return true;
7298 
7299  PHIVals.push_back(std::make_pair(Op0, cast<BasicBlock>(Op1)));
7300  }
7301 
7302  PHINode *PN = PHINode::Create(Ty, PHIVals.size());
7303  for (unsigned i = 0, e = PHIVals.size(); i != e; ++i)
7304  PN->addIncoming(PHIVals[i].first, PHIVals[i].second);
7305  Inst = PN;
7306  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7307 }
7308 
7309 /// parseLandingPad
7310 /// ::= 'landingpad' Type 'personality' TypeAndValue 'cleanup'? Clause+
7311 /// Clause
7312 /// ::= 'catch' TypeAndValue
7313 /// ::= 'filter'
7314 /// ::= 'filter' TypeAndValue ( ',' TypeAndValue )*
7315 bool LLParser::parseLandingPad(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7316  Type *Ty = nullptr; LocTy TyLoc;
7317 
7318  if (parseType(Ty, TyLoc))
7319  return true;
7320 
7321  std::unique_ptr<LandingPadInst> LP(LandingPadInst::Create(Ty, 0));
7322  LP->setCleanup(EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_cleanup));
7323 
7324  while (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_catch || Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_filter){
7325  LandingPadInst::ClauseType CT;
7326  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_catch))
7327  CT = LandingPadInst::Catch;
7328  else if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_filter))
7329  CT = LandingPadInst::Filter;
7330  else
7331  return tokError("expected 'catch' or 'filter' clause type");
7332 
7333  Value *V;
7334  LocTy VLoc;
7335  if (parseTypeAndValue(V, VLoc, PFS))
7336  return true;
7337 
7338  // A 'catch' type expects a non-array constant. A filter clause expects an
7339  // array constant.
7340  if (CT == LandingPadInst::Catch) {
7341  if (isa<ArrayType>(V->getType()))
7342  error(VLoc, "'catch' clause has an invalid type");
7343  } else {
7344  if (!isa<ArrayType>(V->getType()))
7345  error(VLoc, "'filter' clause has an invalid type");
7346  }
7347 
7348  Constant *CV = dyn_cast<Constant>(V);
7349  if (!CV)
7350  return error(VLoc, "clause argument must be a constant");
7351  LP->addClause(CV);
7352  }
7353 
7354  Inst = LP.release();
7355  return false;
7356 }

7358 /// parseFreeze
7359 /// ::= 'freeze' Type Value
7360 bool LLParser::parseFreeze(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7361  LocTy Loc;
7362  Value *Op;
7363  if (parseTypeAndValue(Op, Loc, PFS))
7364  return true;
7365 
7366  Inst = new FreezeInst(Op);
7367  return false;
7368 }

7370 /// parseCall
7371 /// ::= 'call' OptionalFastMathFlags OptionalCallingConv
7372 /// OptionalAttrs Type Value ParameterList OptionalAttrs
7373 /// ::= 'tail' 'call' OptionalFastMathFlags OptionalCallingConv
7374 /// OptionalAttrs Type Value ParameterList OptionalAttrs
7375 /// ::= 'musttail' 'call' OptionalFastMathFlags OptionalCallingConv
7376 /// OptionalAttrs Type Value ParameterList OptionalAttrs
7377 /// ::= 'notail' 'call' OptionalFastMathFlags OptionalCallingConv
7378 /// OptionalAttrs Type Value ParameterList OptionalAttrs
7379 bool LLParser::parseCall(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS,
7380  CallInst::TailCallKind TCK) {
7381  AttrBuilder RetAttrs(M->getContext()), FnAttrs(M->getContext());
7382  std::vector<unsigned> FwdRefAttrGrps;
7383  LocTy BuiltinLoc;
7384  unsigned CallAddrSpace;
7385  unsigned CC;
7386  Type *RetType = nullptr;
7387  LocTy RetTypeLoc;
7388  ValID CalleeID;
7389  SmallVector<ParamInfo, 16> ArgList;
7390  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> BundleList;
7391  LocTy CallLoc = Lex.getLoc();
7392 
7393  if (TCK != CallInst::TCK_None &&
7394  parseToken(lltok::kw_call,
7395  "expected 'tail call', 'musttail call', or 'notail call'"))
7396  return true;
7397 
7398  FastMathFlags FMF = EatFastMathFlagsIfPresent();
7399 
7400  if (parseOptionalCallingConv(CC) || parseOptionalReturnAttrs(RetAttrs) ||
7401  parseOptionalProgramAddrSpace(CallAddrSpace) ||
7402  parseType(RetType, RetTypeLoc, true /*void allowed*/) ||
7403  parseValID(CalleeID, &PFS) ||
7404  parseParameterList(ArgList, PFS, TCK == CallInst::TCK_MustTail,
7405  PFS.getFunction().isVarArg()) ||
7406  parseFnAttributeValuePairs(FnAttrs, FwdRefAttrGrps, false, BuiltinLoc) ||
7407  parseOptionalOperandBundles(BundleList, PFS))
7408  return true;
7409 
7410  // If RetType is a non-function pointer type, then this is the short syntax
7411  // for the call, which means that RetType is just the return type. Infer the
7412  // rest of the function argument types from the arguments that are present.
7413  FunctionType *Ty;
7414  if (resolveFunctionType(RetType, ArgList, Ty))
7415  return error(RetTypeLoc, "Invalid result type for LLVM function");
7416 
7417  CalleeID.FTy = Ty;
7418 
7419  // Look up the callee.
7420  Value *Callee;
7421  if (convertValIDToValue(PointerType::get(Ty, CallAddrSpace), CalleeID, Callee,
7422  &PFS))
7423  return true;
7424 
7425  // Set up the Attribute for the function.
7426  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> Attrs;
7427 
7428  SmallVector<Value*, 8> Args;
7429 
7430  // Loop through FunctionType's arguments and ensure they are specified
7431  // correctly. Also, gather any parameter attributes.
7432  FunctionType::param_iterator I = Ty->param_begin();
7433  FunctionType::param_iterator E = Ty->param_end();
7434  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7435  Type *ExpectedTy = nullptr;
7436  if (I != E) {
7437  ExpectedTy = *I++;
7438  } else if (!Ty->isVarArg()) {
7439  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "too many arguments specified");
7440  }
7441 
7442  if (ExpectedTy && ExpectedTy != ArgList[i].V->getType())
7443  return error(ArgList[i].Loc, "argument is not of expected type '" +
7444  getTypeString(ExpectedTy) + "'");
7445  Args.push_back(ArgList[i].V);
7446  Attrs.push_back(ArgList[i].Attrs);
7447  }
7448 
7449  if (I != E)
7450  return error(CallLoc, "not enough parameters specified for call");
7451 
7452  // Finish off the Attribute and check them
7453  AttributeList PAL =
7454  AttributeList::get(Context, AttributeSet::get(Context, FnAttrs),
7455  AttributeSet::get(Context, RetAttrs), Attrs);
7456 
7457  CallInst *CI = CallInst::Create(Ty, Callee, Args, BundleList);
7458  CI->setTailCallKind(TCK);
7459  CI->setCallingConv(CC);
7460  if (FMF.any()) {
7461  if (!isa<FPMathOperator>(CI)) {
7462  CI->deleteValue();
7463  return error(CallLoc, "fast-math-flags specified for call without "
7464  "floating-point scalar or vector return type");
7465  }
7466  CI->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
7467  }
7468  CI->setAttributes(PAL);
7469  ForwardRefAttrGroups[CI] = FwdRefAttrGrps;
7470  Inst = CI;
7471  return false;
7472 }

7478 /// parseAlloc
7479 /// ::= 'alloca' 'inalloca'? 'swifterror'? Type (',' TypeAndValue)?
7480 /// (',' 'align' i32)? (',', 'addrspace(n))?
7481 int LLParser::parseAlloc(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7482  Value *Size = nullptr;
7483  LocTy SizeLoc, TyLoc, ASLoc;
7484  MaybeAlign Alignment;
7485  unsigned AddrSpace = 0;
7486  Type *Ty = nullptr;
7487 
7488  bool IsInAlloca = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inalloca);
7489  bool IsSwiftError = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_swifterror);
7490 
7491  if (parseType(Ty, TyLoc))
7492  return true;
7493 
7494  if (Ty->isFunctionTy() || !PointerType::isValidElementType(Ty))
7495  return error(TyLoc, "invalid type for alloca");
7496 
7497  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7498  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7499  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_align) {
7500  if (parseOptionalAlignment(Alignment))
7501  return true;
7502  if (parseOptionalCommaAddrSpace(AddrSpace, ASLoc, AteExtraComma))
7503  return true;
7504  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_addrspace) {
7505  ASLoc = Lex.getLoc();
7506  if (parseOptionalAddrSpace(AddrSpace))
7507  return true;
7508  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
7509  AteExtraComma = true;
7510  } else {
7511  if (parseTypeAndValue(Size, SizeLoc, PFS))
7512  return true;
7513  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7514  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_align) {
7515  if (parseOptionalAlignment(Alignment))
7516  return true;
7517  if (parseOptionalCommaAddrSpace(AddrSpace, ASLoc, AteExtraComma))
7518  return true;
7519  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_addrspace) {
7520  ASLoc = Lex.getLoc();
7521  if (parseOptionalAddrSpace(AddrSpace))
7522  return true;
7523  } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
7524  AteExtraComma = true;
7525  }
7526  }
7527  }
7528  }
7529 
7530  if (Size && !Size->getType()->isIntegerTy())
7531  return error(SizeLoc, "element count must have integer type");
7532 
7533  SmallPtrSet<Type *, 4> Visited;
7534  if (!Alignment && !Ty->isSized(&Visited))
7535  return error(TyLoc, "Cannot allocate unsized type");
7536  if (!Alignment)
7537  Alignment = M->getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(Ty);
7538  AllocaInst *AI = new AllocaInst(Ty, AddrSpace, Size, *Alignment);
7539  AI->setUsedWithInAlloca(IsInAlloca);
7540  AI->setSwiftError(IsSwiftError);
7541  Inst = AI;
7542  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7543 }
7544 
7545 /// parseLoad
7546 /// ::= 'load' 'volatile'? TypeAndValue (',' 'align' i32)?
7547 /// ::= 'load' 'atomic' 'volatile'? TypeAndValue
7548 /// 'singlethread'? AtomicOrdering (',' 'align' i32)?
7549 int LLParser::parseLoad(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7550  Value *Val; LocTy Loc;
7551  MaybeAlign Alignment;
7552  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7553  bool isAtomic = false;
7554  AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7555  SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System;
7556 
7557  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_atomic) {
7558  isAtomic = true;
7559  Lex.Lex();
7560  }
7561 
7562  bool isVolatile = false;
7563  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_volatile) {
7564  isVolatile = true;
7565  Lex.Lex();
7566  }
7567 
7568  Type *Ty;
7569  LocTy ExplicitTypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
7570  if (parseType(Ty) ||
7571  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma after load's type") ||
7572  parseTypeAndValue(Val, Loc, PFS) ||
7573  parseScopeAndOrdering(isAtomic, SSID, Ordering) ||
7574  parseOptionalCommaAlign(Alignment, AteExtraComma))
7575  return true;
7576 
7577  if (!Val->getType()->isPointerTy() || !Ty->isFirstClassType())
7578  return error(Loc, "load operand must be a pointer to a first class type");
7579  if (isAtomic && !Alignment)
7580  return error(Loc, "atomic load must have explicit non-zero alignment");
7581  if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Release ||
7582  Ordering == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease)
7583  return error(Loc, "atomic load cannot use Release ordering");
7584 
7585  if (!cast<PointerType>(Val->getType())->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Ty)) {
7586  return error(
7587  ExplicitTypeLoc,
7588  typeComparisonErrorMessage(
7589  "explicit pointee type doesn't match operand's pointee type", Ty,
7590  Val->getType()->getNonOpaquePointerElementType()));
7591  }
7592  SmallPtrSet<Type *, 4> Visited;
7593  if (!Alignment && !Ty->isSized(&Visited))
7594  return error(ExplicitTypeLoc, "loading unsized types is not allowed");
7595  if (!Alignment)
7596  Alignment = M->getDataLayout().getABITypeAlign(Ty);
7597  Inst = new LoadInst(Ty, Val, "", isVolatile, *Alignment, Ordering, SSID);
7598  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7599 }

7601 /// parseStore
7602 
7603 /// ::= 'store' 'volatile'? TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue (',' 'align' i32)?
7604 /// ::= 'store' 'atomic' 'volatile'? TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue
7605 /// 'singlethread'? AtomicOrdering (',' 'align' i32)?
7606 int LLParser::parseStore(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7607  Value *Val, *Ptr; LocTy Loc, PtrLoc;
7608  MaybeAlign Alignment;
7609  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7610  bool isAtomic = false;
7611  AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7612  SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System;
7613 
7614  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_atomic) {
7615  isAtomic = true;
7616  Lex.Lex();
7617  }
7618 
7619  bool isVolatile = false;
7620  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_volatile) {
7621  isVolatile = true;
7622  Lex.Lex();
7623  }
7624 
7625  if (parseTypeAndValue(Val, Loc, PFS) ||
7626  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after store operand") ||
7627  parseTypeAndValue(Ptr, PtrLoc, PFS) ||
7628  parseScopeAndOrdering(isAtomic, SSID, Ordering) ||
7629  parseOptionalCommaAlign(Alignment, AteExtraComma))
7630  return true;
7631 
7632  if (!Ptr->getType()->isPointerTy())
7633  return error(PtrLoc, "store operand must be a pointer");
7634  if (!Val->getType()->isFirstClassType())
7635  return error(Loc, "store operand must be a first class value");
7636  if (!cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())
7637  ->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Val->getType()))
7638  return error(Loc, "stored value and pointer type do not match");
7639  if (isAtomic && !Alignment)
7640  return error(Loc, "atomic store must have explicit non-zero alignment");
7641  if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Acquire ||
7642  Ordering == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease)
7643  return error(Loc, "atomic store cannot use Acquire ordering");
7644  SmallPtrSet<Type *, 4> Visited;
7645  if (!Alignment && !Val->getType()->isSized(&Visited))
7646  return error(Loc, "storing unsized types is not allowed");
7647  if (!Alignment)
7648  Alignment = M->getDataLayout().getABITypeAlign(Val->getType());
7649 
7650  Inst = new StoreInst(Val, Ptr, isVolatile, *Alignment, Ordering, SSID);
7651  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7652 }
7653 
7654 /// parseCmpXchg
7655 /// ::= 'cmpxchg' 'weak'? 'volatile'? TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue ','
7656 /// TypeAndValue 'singlethread'? AtomicOrdering AtomicOrdering ','
7657 /// 'Align'?
7658 int LLParser::parseCmpXchg(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7659  Value *Ptr, *Cmp, *New; LocTy PtrLoc, CmpLoc, NewLoc;
7660  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7661  AtomicOrdering SuccessOrdering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7662  AtomicOrdering FailureOrdering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7663  SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System;
7664  bool isVolatile = false;
7665  bool isWeak = false;
7666  MaybeAlign Alignment;
7667 
7668  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_weak))
7669  isWeak = true;
7670 
7671  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_volatile))
7672  isVolatile = true;
7673 
7674  if (parseTypeAndValue(Ptr, PtrLoc, PFS) ||
7675  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after cmpxchg address") ||
7676  parseTypeAndValue(Cmp, CmpLoc, PFS) ||
7677  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after cmpxchg cmp operand") ||
7678  parseTypeAndValue(New, NewLoc, PFS) ||
7679  parseScopeAndOrdering(true /*Always atomic*/, SSID, SuccessOrdering) ||
7680  parseOrdering(FailureOrdering) ||
7681  parseOptionalCommaAlign(Alignment, AteExtraComma))
7682  return true;
7683 
7684  if (!AtomicCmpXchgInst::isValidSuccessOrdering(SuccessOrdering))
7685  return tokError("invalid cmpxchg success ordering");
7686  if (!AtomicCmpXchgInst::isValidFailureOrdering(FailureOrdering))
7687  return tokError("invalid cmpxchg failure ordering");
7688  if (!Ptr->getType()->isPointerTy())
7689  return error(PtrLoc, "cmpxchg operand must be a pointer");
7690  if (!cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())
7691  ->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Cmp->getType()))
7692  return error(CmpLoc, "compare value and pointer type do not match");
7693  if (!cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())
7694  ->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(New->getType()))
7695  return error(NewLoc, "new value and pointer type do not match");
7696  if (Cmp->getType() != New->getType())
7697  return error(NewLoc, "compare value and new value type do not match");
7698  if (!New->getType()->isFirstClassType())
7699  return error(NewLoc, "cmpxchg operand must be a first class value");
7700 
7701  const Align DefaultAlignment(
7702  PFS.getFunction().getParent()->getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(
7703  Cmp->getType()));
7704 
7705  AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI =
7706  new AtomicCmpXchgInst(Ptr, Cmp, New, Alignment.value_or(DefaultAlignment),
7707  SuccessOrdering, FailureOrdering, SSID);
7708  CXI->setVolatile(isVolatile);
7709  CXI->setWeak(isWeak);
7710 
7711  Inst = CXI;
7712  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7713 }
7714 
7715 /// parseAtomicRMW
7716 /// ::= 'atomicrmw' 'volatile'? BinOp TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue
7717 /// 'singlethread'? AtomicOrdering
7718 int LLParser::parseAtomicRMW(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7719  Value *Ptr, *Val; LocTy PtrLoc, ValLoc;
7720  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7721  AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7722  SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System;
7723  bool isVolatile = false;
7724  bool IsFP = false;
7725  AtomicRMWInst::BinOp Operation;
7726  MaybeAlign Alignment;
7727 
7728  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_volatile))
7729  isVolatile = true;
7730 
7731  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7732  default:
7733  return tokError("expected binary operation in atomicrmw");
7734  case lltok::kw_xchg: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Xchg; break;
7735  case lltok::kw_add: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Add; break;
7736  case lltok::kw_sub: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Sub; break;
7737  case lltok::kw_and: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::And; break;
7738  case lltok::kw_nand: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Nand; break;
7739  case lltok::kw_or: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Or; break;
7740  case lltok::kw_xor: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Xor; break;
7741  case lltok::kw_max: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Max; break;
7742  case lltok::kw_min: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::Min; break;
7743  case lltok::kw_umax: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::UMax; break;
7744  case lltok::kw_umin: Operation = AtomicRMWInst::UMin; break;
7745  case lltok::kw_uinc_wrap:
7746  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::UIncWrap;
7747  break;
7748  case lltok::kw_udec_wrap:
7749  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::UDecWrap;
7750  break;
7751  case lltok::kw_fadd:
7752  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::FAdd;
7753  IsFP = true;
7754  break;
7755  case lltok::kw_fsub:
7756  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::FSub;
7757  IsFP = true;
7758  break;
7759  case lltok::kw_fmax:
7760  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::FMax;
7761  IsFP = true;
7762  break;
7763  case lltok::kw_fmin:
7764  Operation = AtomicRMWInst::FMin;
7765  IsFP = true;
7766  break;
7767  }
7768  Lex.Lex(); // Eat the operation.
7769 
7770  if (parseTypeAndValue(Ptr, PtrLoc, PFS) ||
7771  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' after atomicrmw address") ||
7772  parseTypeAndValue(Val, ValLoc, PFS) ||
7773  parseScopeAndOrdering(true /*Always atomic*/, SSID, Ordering) ||
7774  parseOptionalCommaAlign(Alignment, AteExtraComma))
7775  return true;
7776 
7777  if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Unordered)
7778  return tokError("atomicrmw cannot be unordered");
7779  if (!Ptr->getType()->isPointerTy())
7780  return error(PtrLoc, "atomicrmw operand must be a pointer");
7781  if (!cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())
7782  ->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Val->getType()))
7783  return error(ValLoc, "atomicrmw value and pointer type do not match");
7784 
7785  if (Operation == AtomicRMWInst::Xchg) {
7786  if (!Val->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
7787  !Val->getType()->isFloatingPointTy() &&
7788  !Val->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
7789  return error(
7790  ValLoc,
7791  "atomicrmw " + AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(Operation) +
7792  " operand must be an integer, floating point, or pointer type");
7793  }
7794  } else if (IsFP) {
7795  if (!Val->getType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
7796  return error(ValLoc, "atomicrmw " +
7797  AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(Operation) +
7798  " operand must be a floating point type");
7799  }
7800  } else {
7801  if (!Val->getType()->isIntegerTy()) {
7802  return error(ValLoc, "atomicrmw " +
7803  AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(Operation) +
7804  " operand must be an integer");
7805  }
7806  }
7807 
7808  unsigned Size =
7809  PFS.getFunction().getParent()->getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSizeInBits(
7810  Val->getType());
7811  if (Size < 8 || (Size & (Size - 1)))
7812  return error(ValLoc, "atomicrmw operand must be power-of-two byte-sized"
7813  " integer");
7814  const Align DefaultAlignment(
7815  PFS.getFunction().getParent()->getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(
7816  Val->getType()));
7817  AtomicRMWInst *RMWI =
7818  new AtomicRMWInst(Operation, Ptr, Val,
7819  Alignment.value_or(DefaultAlignment), Ordering, SSID);
7820  RMWI->setVolatile(isVolatile);
7821  Inst = RMWI;
7822  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7823 }
7824 
7825 /// parseFence
7826 /// ::= 'fence' 'singlethread'? AtomicOrdering
7827 int LLParser::parseFence(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7828  AtomicOrdering Ordering = AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic;
7829  SyncScope::ID SSID = SyncScope::System;
7830  if (parseScopeAndOrdering(true /*Always atomic*/, SSID, Ordering))
7831  return true;
7832 
7833  if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Unordered)
7834  return tokError("fence cannot be unordered");
7835  if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Monotonic)
7836  return tokError("fence cannot be monotonic");
7837 
7838  Inst = new FenceInst(Context, Ordering, SSID);
7839  return InstNormal;
7840 }

7842 /// parseGetElementPtr
7843 /// ::= 'getelementptr' 'inbounds'? TypeAndValue (',' TypeAndValue)*
7844 int LLParser::parseGetElementPtr(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7845  Value *Ptr = nullptr;
7846  Value *Val = nullptr;
7847  LocTy Loc, EltLoc;
7848 
7849  bool InBounds = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inbounds);
7850 
7851  Type *Ty = nullptr;
7852  LocTy ExplicitTypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
7853  if (parseType(Ty) ||
7854  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma after getelementptr's type") ||
7855  parseTypeAndValue(Ptr, Loc, PFS))
7856  return true;
7857 
7858  Type *BaseType = Ptr->getType();
7859  PointerType *BasePointerType = dyn_cast<PointerType>(BaseType->getScalarType());
7860  if (!BasePointerType)
7861  return error(Loc, "base of getelementptr must be a pointer");
7862 
7863  if (!BasePointerType->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Ty)) {
7864  return error(
7865  ExplicitTypeLoc,
7866  typeComparisonErrorMessage(
7867  "explicit pointee type doesn't match operand's pointee type", Ty,
7868  BasePointerType->getNonOpaquePointerElementType()));
7869  }
7870 
7871  SmallVector<Value*, 16> Indices;
7872  bool AteExtraComma = false;
7873  // GEP returns a vector of pointers if at least one of parameters is a vector.
7874  // All vector parameters should have the same vector width.
7875  ElementCount GEPWidth = BaseType->isVectorTy()
7876  ? cast<VectorType>(BaseType)->getElementCount()
7877  : ElementCount::getFixed(0);
7878 
7879  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7880  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
7881  AteExtraComma = true;
7882  break;
7883  }
7884  if (parseTypeAndValue(Val, EltLoc, PFS))
7885  return true;
7886  if (!Val->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
7887  return error(EltLoc, "getelementptr index must be an integer");
7888 
7889  if (auto *ValVTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Val->getType())) {
7890  ElementCount ValNumEl = ValVTy->getElementCount();
7891  if (GEPWidth != ElementCount::getFixed(0) && GEPWidth != ValNumEl)
7892  return error(
7893  EltLoc,
7894  "getelementptr vector index has a wrong number of elements");
7895  GEPWidth = ValNumEl;
7896  }
7897  Indices.push_back(Val);
7898  }
7899 
7900  SmallPtrSet<Type*, 4> Visited;
7901  if (!Indices.empty() && !Ty->isSized(&Visited))
7902  return error(Loc, "base element of getelementptr must be sized");
7903 
7904  if (!GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(Ty, Indices))
7905  return error(Loc, "invalid getelementptr indices");
7906  Inst = GetElementPtrInst::Create(Ty, Ptr, Indices);
7907  if (InBounds)
7908  cast<GetElementPtrInst>(Inst)->setIsInBounds(true);
7909  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7910 }

7912 /// parseExtractValue
7913 /// ::= 'extractvalue' TypeAndValue (',' uint32)+
7914 int LLParser::parseExtractValue(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7915  Value *Val; LocTy Loc;
7916  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Indices;
7917  bool AteExtraComma;
7918  if (parseTypeAndValue(Val, Loc, PFS) ||
7919  parseIndexList(Indices, AteExtraComma))
7920  return true;
7921 
7922  if (!Val->getType()->isAggregateType())
7923  return error(Loc, "extractvalue operand must be aggregate type");
7924 
7925  if (!ExtractValueInst::getIndexedType(Val->getType(), Indices))
7926  return error(Loc, "invalid indices for extractvalue");
7927  Inst = ExtractValueInst::Create(Val, Indices);
7928  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7929 }

7931 /// parseInsertValue
7932 /// ::= 'insertvalue' TypeAndValue ',' TypeAndValue (',' uint32)+
7933 int LLParser::parseInsertValue(Instruction *&Inst, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
7934  Value *Val0, *Val1; LocTy Loc0, Loc1;
7935  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Indices;
7936  bool AteExtraComma;
7937  if (parseTypeAndValue(Val0, Loc0, PFS) ||
7938  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma after insertvalue operand") ||
7939  parseTypeAndValue(Val1, Loc1, PFS) ||
7940  parseIndexList(Indices, AteExtraComma))
7941  return true;
7942 
7943  if (!Val0->getType()->isAggregateType())
7944  return error(Loc0, "insertvalue operand must be aggregate type");
7945 
7946  Type *IndexedType = ExtractValueInst::getIndexedType(Val0->getType(), Indices);
7947  if (!IndexedType)
7948  return error(Loc0, "invalid indices for insertvalue");
7949  if (IndexedType != Val1->getType())
7950  return error(Loc1, "insertvalue operand and field disagree in type: '" +
7951  getTypeString(Val1->getType()) + "' instead of '" +
7952  getTypeString(IndexedType) + "'");
7953  Inst = InsertValueInst::Create(Val0, Val1, Indices);
7954  return AteExtraComma ? InstExtraComma : InstNormal;
7955 }

7961 /// parseMDNodeVector
7962 /// ::= { Element (',' Element)* }
7963 /// Element
7964 /// ::= 'null' | TypeAndValue
7965 bool LLParser::parseMDNodeVector(SmallVectorImpl<Metadata *> &Elts) {
7966  if (parseToken(lltok::lbrace, "expected '{' here"))
7967  return true;
7968 
7969  // Check for an empty list.
7970  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::rbrace))
7971  return false;
7972 
7973  do {
7974  // Null is a special case since it is typeless.
7975  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_null)) {
7976  Elts.push_back(nullptr);
7977  continue;
7978  }
7979 
7980  Metadata *MD;
7981  if (parseMetadata(MD, nullptr))
7982  return true;
7983  Elts.push_back(MD);
7984  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7985 
7986  return parseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of metadata node");
7987 }
7988 
7989 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7990 // Use-list order directives.
7991 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7992 bool LLParser::sortUseListOrder(Value *V, ArrayRef<unsigned> Indexes,
7993  SMLoc Loc) {
7994  if (V->use_empty())
7995  return error(Loc, "value has no uses");
7996 
7997  unsigned NumUses = 0;
7998  SmallDenseMap<const Use *, unsigned, 16> Order;
7999  for (const Use &U : V->uses()) {
8000  if (++NumUses > Indexes.size())
8001  break;
8002  Order[&U] = Indexes[NumUses - 1];
8003  }
8004  if (NumUses < 2)
8005  return error(Loc, "value only has one use");
8006  if (Order.size() != Indexes.size() || NumUses > Indexes.size())
8007  return error(Loc,
8008  "wrong number of indexes, expected " + Twine(V->getNumUses()));
8009 
8010  V->sortUseList([&](const Use &L, const Use &R) {
8011  return Order.lookup(&L) < Order.lookup(&R);
8012  });
8013  return false;
8014 }
8015 
8016 /// parseUseListOrderIndexes
8017 /// ::= '{' uint32 (',' uint32)+ '}'
8018 bool LLParser::parseUseListOrderIndexes(SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &Indexes) {
8019  SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8020  if (parseToken(lltok::lbrace, "expected '{' here"))
8021  return true;
8022  if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rbrace)
8023  return Lex.Error("expected non-empty list of uselistorder indexes");
8024 
8025  // Use Offset, Max, and IsOrdered to check consistency of indexes. The
8026  // indexes should be distinct numbers in the range [0, size-1], and should
8027  // not be in order.
8028  unsigned Offset = 0;
8029  unsigned Max = 0;
8030  bool IsOrdered = true;
8031  assert(Indexes.empty() && "Expected empty order vector");
8032  do {
8033  unsigned Index;
8034  if (parseUInt32(Index))
8035  return true;
8036 
8037  // Update consistency checks.
8038  Offset += Index - Indexes.size();
8039  Max = std::max(Max, Index);
8040  IsOrdered &= Index == Indexes.size();
8041 
8042  Indexes.push_back(Index);
8043  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8044 
8045  if (parseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected '}' here"))
8046  return true;
8047 
8048  if (Indexes.size() < 2)
8049  return error(Loc, "expected >= 2 uselistorder indexes");
8050  if (Offset != 0 || Max >= Indexes.size())
8051  return error(Loc,
8052  "expected distinct uselistorder indexes in range [0, size)");
8053  if (IsOrdered)
8054  return error(Loc, "expected uselistorder indexes to change the order");
8055 
8056  return false;
8057 }
8058 
8059 /// parseUseListOrder
8060 /// ::= 'uselistorder' Type Value ',' UseListOrderIndexes
8061 bool LLParser::parseUseListOrder(PerFunctionState *PFS) {
8062  SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8063  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_uselistorder, "expected uselistorder directive"))
8064  return true;
8065 
8066  Value *V;
8067  SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Indexes;
8068  if (parseTypeAndValue(V, PFS) ||
8069  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder directive") ||
8070  parseUseListOrderIndexes(Indexes))
8071  return true;
8072 
8073  return sortUseListOrder(V, Indexes, Loc);
8074 }
8075 
8076 /// parseUseListOrderBB
8077 /// ::= 'uselistorder_bb' @foo ',' %bar ',' UseListOrderIndexes
8078 bool LLParser::parseUseListOrderBB() {
8079  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_uselistorder_bb);
8080  SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8081  Lex.Lex();
8082 
8083  ValID Fn, Label;
8084  SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Indexes;
8085  if (parseValID(Fn, /*PFS=*/nullptr) ||
8086  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder_bb directive") ||
8087  parseValID(Label, /*PFS=*/nullptr) ||
8088  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder_bb directive") ||
8089  parseUseListOrderIndexes(Indexes))
8090  return true;
8091 
8092  // Check the function.
8093  GlobalValue *GV;
8094  if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalName)
8095  GV = M->getNamedValue(Fn.StrVal);
8096  else if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID)
8097  GV = Fn.UIntVal < NumberedVals.size() ? NumberedVals[Fn.UIntVal] : nullptr;
8098  else
8099  return error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in uselistorder_bb");
8100  if (!GV)
8101  return error(Fn.Loc,
8102  "invalid function forward reference in uselistorder_bb");
8103  auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(GV);
8104  if (!F)
8105  return error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in uselistorder_bb");
8106  if (F->isDeclaration())
8107  return error(Fn.Loc, "invalid declaration in uselistorder_bb");
8108 
8109  // Check the basic block.
8110  if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
8111  return error(Label.Loc, "invalid numeric label in uselistorder_bb");
8112  if (Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalName)
8113  return error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block name in uselistorder_bb");
8114  Value *V = F->getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Label.StrVal);
8115  if (!V)
8116  return error(Label.Loc, "invalid basic block in uselistorder_bb");
8117  if (!isa<BasicBlock>(V))
8118  return error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block in uselistorder_bb");
8119 
8120  return sortUseListOrder(V, Indexes, Loc);
8121 }

8123 /// ModuleEntry
8124 /// ::= 'module' ':' '(' 'path' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ',' 'hash' ':' Hash ')'
8125 /// Hash ::= '(' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ')'
8126 bool LLParser::parseModuleEntry(unsigned ID) {
8127  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_module);
8128  Lex.Lex();
8129 
8130  std::string Path;
8131  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8132  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8133  parseToken(lltok::kw_path, "expected 'path' here") ||
8134  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8135  parseStringConstant(Path) ||
8136  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8137  parseToken(lltok::kw_hash, "expected 'hash' here") ||
8138  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8139  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8140  return true;
8141 
8142  ModuleHash Hash;
8143  if (parseUInt32(Hash[0]) || parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8144  parseUInt32(Hash[1]) || parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8145  parseUInt32(Hash[2]) || parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8146  parseUInt32(Hash[3]) || parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8147  parseUInt32(Hash[4]))
8148  return true;
8149 
8150  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here") ||
8151  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8152  return true;
8153 
8154  auto ModuleEntry = Index->addModule(Path, ID, Hash);
8155  ModuleIdMap[ID] = ModuleEntry->first();
8156 
8157  return false;
8158 }

8160 /// TypeIdEntry
8161 /// ::= 'typeid' ':' '(' 'name' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ',' TypeIdSummary ')'
8162 bool LLParser::parseTypeIdEntry(unsigned ID) {
8163  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeid);
8164  Lex.Lex();
8165 
8166  std::string Name;
8167  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8168  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8169  parseToken(lltok::kw_name, "expected 'name' here") ||
8170  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8171  parseStringConstant(Name))
8172  return true;
8173 
8174  TypeIdSummary &TIS = Index->getOrInsertTypeIdSummary(Name);
8175  if (parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8176  parseTypeIdSummary(TIS) || parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8177  return true;
8178 
8179  // Check if this ID was forward referenced, and if so, update the
8180  // corresponding GUIDs.
8181  auto FwdRefTIDs = ForwardRefTypeIds.find(ID);
8182  if (FwdRefTIDs != ForwardRefTypeIds.end()) {
8183  for (auto TIDRef : FwdRefTIDs->second) {
8184  assert(!*TIDRef.first &&
8185  "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
8186  *TIDRef.first = GlobalValue::getGUID(Name);
8187  }
8188  ForwardRefTypeIds.erase(FwdRefTIDs);
8189  }
8190 
8191  return false;
8192 }
