8194 /// TypeIdSummary
8195 /// ::= 'summary' ':' '(' TypeTestResolution [',' OptionalWpdResolutions]? ')'
8196 bool LLParser::parseTypeIdSummary(TypeIdSummary &TIS) {
8197  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_summary, "expected 'summary' here") ||
8198  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8199  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8200  parseTypeTestResolution(TIS.TTRes))
8201  return true;
8202 
8203  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8204  // Expect optional wpdResolutions field
8205  if (parseOptionalWpdResolutions(TIS.WPDRes))
8206  return true;
8207  }
8208 
8209  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8210  return true;
8211 
8212  return false;
8213 }
8214 
8215 static ValueInfo EmptyVI =
8216  ValueInfo(false, (GlobalValueSummaryMapTy::value_type *)-8);
8217 
8218 /// TypeIdCompatibleVtableEntry
8219 /// ::= 'typeidCompatibleVTable' ':' '(' 'name' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ','
8220 /// TypeIdCompatibleVtableInfo
8221 /// ')'
8222 bool LLParser::parseTypeIdCompatibleVtableEntry(unsigned ID) {
8223  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeidCompatibleVTable);
8224  Lex.Lex();
8225 
8226  std::string Name;
8227  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8228  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8229  parseToken(lltok::kw_name, "expected 'name' here") ||
8230  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8231  parseStringConstant(Name))
8232  return true;
8233 
8234  TypeIdCompatibleVtableInfo &TI =
8235  Index->getOrInsertTypeIdCompatibleVtableSummary(Name);
8236  if (parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8237  parseToken(lltok::kw_summary, "expected 'summary' here") ||
8238  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8239  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8240  return true;
8241 
8242  IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8243  // parse each call edge
8244  do {
8245  uint64_t Offset;
8246  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8247  parseToken(lltok::kw_offset, "expected 'offset' here") ||
8248  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || parseUInt64(Offset) ||
8249  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here"))
8250  return true;
8251 
8252  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8253  unsigned GVId;
8254  ValueInfo VI;
8255  if (parseGVReference(VI, GVId))
8256  return true;
8257 
8258  // Keep track of the TypeIdCompatibleVtableInfo array index needing a
8259  // forward reference. We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an
8260  // update, but can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
8261  if (VI == EmptyVI)
8262  IdToIndexMap[GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(TI.size(), Loc));
8263  TI.push_back({Offset, VI});
8264 
8265  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in call"))
8266  return true;
8267  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8268 
8269  // Now that the TI vector is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
8270  // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8271  for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8272  auto &Infos = ForwardRefValueInfos[I.first];
8273  for (auto P : I.second) {
8274  assert(TI[P.first].VTableVI == EmptyVI &&
8275  "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
8276  Infos.emplace_back(&TI[P.first].VTableVI, P.second);
8277  }
8278  }
8279 
8280  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here") ||
8281  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8282  return true;
8283 
8284  // Check if this ID was forward referenced, and if so, update the
8285  // corresponding GUIDs.
8286  auto FwdRefTIDs = ForwardRefTypeIds.find(ID);
8287  if (FwdRefTIDs != ForwardRefTypeIds.end()) {
8288  for (auto TIDRef : FwdRefTIDs->second) {
8289  assert(!*TIDRef.first &&
8290  "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
8291  *TIDRef.first = GlobalValue::getGUID(Name);
8292  }
8293  ForwardRefTypeIds.erase(FwdRefTIDs);
8294  }
8295 
8296  return false;
8297 }

8572 static const auto FwdVIRef = (GlobalValueSummaryMapTy::value_type *)-8;
8573 
8574 static void resolveFwdRef(ValueInfo *Fwd, ValueInfo &Resolved) {
8575  bool ReadOnly = Fwd->isReadOnly();
8576  bool WriteOnly = Fwd->isWriteOnly();
8577  assert(!(ReadOnly && WriteOnly));
8578  *Fwd = Resolved;
8579  if (ReadOnly)
8580  Fwd->setReadOnly();
8581  if (WriteOnly)
8582  Fwd->setWriteOnly();
8583 }

8585 /// Stores the given Name/GUID and associated summary into the Index.
8586 /// Also updates any forward references to the associated entry ID.
8587 void LLParser::addGlobalValueToIndex(
8588  std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage,
8589  unsigned ID, std::unique_ptr<GlobalValueSummary> Summary) {
8590  // First create the ValueInfo utilizing the Name or GUID.
8591  ValueInfo VI;
8592  if (GUID != 0) {
8593  assert(Name.empty());
8594  VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GUID);
8595  } else {
8596  assert(!Name.empty());
8597  if (M) {
8598  auto *GV = M->getNamedValue(Name);
8599  assert(GV);
8600  VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GV);
8601  } else {
8602  assert(
8603  (!GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage) || !SourceFileName.empty()) &&
8604  "Need a source_filename to compute GUID for local");
8605  GUID = GlobalValue::getGUID(
8606  GlobalValue::getGlobalIdentifier(Name, Linkage, SourceFileName));
8607  VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GUID, Index->saveString(Name));
8608  }
8609  }
8610 
8611  // Resolve forward references from calls/refs
8612  auto FwdRefVIs = ForwardRefValueInfos.find(ID);
8613  if (FwdRefVIs != ForwardRefValueInfos.end()) {
8614  for (auto VIRef : FwdRefVIs->second) {
8615  assert(VIRef.first->getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
8616  "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
8617  resolveFwdRef(VIRef.first, VI);
8618  }
8619  ForwardRefValueInfos.erase(FwdRefVIs);
8620  }
8621 
8622  // Resolve forward references from aliases
8623  auto FwdRefAliasees = ForwardRefAliasees.find(ID);
8624  if (FwdRefAliasees != ForwardRefAliasees.end()) {
8625  for (auto AliaseeRef : FwdRefAliasees->second) {
8626  assert(!AliaseeRef.first->hasAliasee() &&
8627  "Forward referencing alias already has aliasee");
8628  assert(Summary && "Aliasee must be a definition");
8629  AliaseeRef.first->setAliasee(VI, Summary.get());
8630  }
8631  ForwardRefAliasees.erase(FwdRefAliasees);
8632  }
8633 
8634  // Add the summary if one was provided.
8635  if (Summary)
8636  Index->addGlobalValueSummary(VI, std::move(Summary));
8637 
8638  // Save the associated ValueInfo for use in later references by ID.
8639  if (ID == NumberedValueInfos.size())
8640  NumberedValueInfos.push_back(VI);
8641  else {
8642  // Handle non-continuous numbers (to make test simplification easier).
8643  if (ID > NumberedValueInfos.size())
8644  NumberedValueInfos.resize(ID + 1);
8645  NumberedValueInfos[ID] = VI;
8646  }
8647 }

8681 /// parseGVEntry
8682 /// ::= 'gv' ':' '(' ('name' ':' STRINGCONSTANT | 'guid' ':' UInt64)
8683 /// [',' 'summaries' ':' Summary[',' Summary]* ]? ')'
8684 /// Summary ::= '(' (FunctionSummary | VariableSummary | AliasSummary) ')'
8685 bool LLParser::parseGVEntry(unsigned ID) {
8686  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_gv);
8687  Lex.Lex();
8688 
8689  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8690  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8691  return true;
8692 
8693  std::string Name;
8694  GlobalValue::GUID GUID = 0;
8695  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8696  case lltok::kw_name:
8697  Lex.Lex();
8698  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8699  parseStringConstant(Name))
8700  return true;
8701  // Can't create GUID/ValueInfo until we have the linkage.
8702  break;
8703  case lltok::kw_guid:
8704  Lex.Lex();
8705  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || parseUInt64(GUID))
8706  return true;
8707  break;
8708  default:
8709  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected name or guid tag");
8710  }
8711 
8712  if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8713  // No summaries. Wrap up.
8714  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8715  return true;
8716  // This was created for a call to an external or indirect target.
8717  // A GUID with no summary came from a VALUE_GUID record, dummy GUID
8718  // created for indirect calls with VP. A Name with no GUID came from
8719  // an external definition. We pass ExternalLinkage since that is only
8720  // used when the GUID must be computed from Name, and in that case
8721  // the symbol must have external linkage.
8722  addGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, ID,
8723  nullptr);
8724  return false;
8725  }
8726 
8727  // Have a list of summaries
8728  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_summaries, "expected 'summaries' here") ||
8729  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8730  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8731  return true;
8732  do {
8733  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8734  case lltok::kw_function:
8735  if (parseFunctionSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
8736  return true;
8737  break;
8738  case lltok::kw_variable:
8739  if (parseVariableSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
8740  return true;
8741  break;
8742  case lltok::kw_alias:
8743  if (parseAliasSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
8744  return true;
8745  break;
8746  default:
8747  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected summary type");
8748  }
8749  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8750 
8751  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here") ||
8752  parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8753  return true;
8754 
8755  return false;
8756 }
8757 
8758 /// FunctionSummary
8759 /// ::= 'function' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags
8760 /// ',' 'insts' ':' UInt32 [',' OptionalFFlags]? [',' OptionalCalls]?
8761 /// [',' OptionalTypeIdInfo]? [',' OptionalParamAccesses]?
8762 /// [',' OptionalRefs]? ')'
8763 bool LLParser::parseFunctionSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
8764  unsigned ID) {
8765  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_function);
8766  Lex.Lex();
8767 
8768  StringRef ModulePath;
8769  GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
8770  GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility,
8771  /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
8772  /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
8773  unsigned InstCount;
8774  std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> Calls;
8775  FunctionSummary::TypeIdInfo TypeIdInfo;
8776  std::vector<FunctionSummary::ParamAccess> ParamAccesses;
8777  std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs;
8778  std::vector<CallsiteInfo> Callsites;
8779  std::vector<AllocInfo> Allocs;
8780  // Default is all-zeros (conservative values).
8781  FunctionSummary::FFlags FFlags = {};
8782  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8783  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8784  parseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
8785  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || parseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
8786  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8787  parseToken(lltok::kw_insts, "expected 'insts' here") ||
8788  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || parseUInt32(InstCount))
8789  return true;
8790 
8791  // parse optional fields
8792  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8793  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8794  case lltok::kw_funcFlags:
8795  if (parseOptionalFFlags(FFlags))
8796  return true;
8797  break;
8798  case lltok::kw_calls:
8799  if (parseOptionalCalls(Calls))
8800  return true;
8801  break;
8802  case lltok::kw_typeIdInfo:
8803  if (parseOptionalTypeIdInfo(TypeIdInfo))
8804  return true;
8805  break;
8806  case lltok::kw_refs:
8807  if (parseOptionalRefs(Refs))
8808  return true;
8809  break;
8810  case lltok::kw_params:
8811  if (parseOptionalParamAccesses(ParamAccesses))
8812  return true;
8813  break;
8814  case lltok::kw_allocs:
8815  if (parseOptionalAllocs(Allocs))
8816  return true;
8817  break;
8818  case lltok::kw_callsites:
8819  if (parseOptionalCallsites(Callsites))
8820  return true;
8821  break;
8822  default:
8823  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected optional function summary field");
8824  }
8825  }
8826 
8827  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8828  return true;
8829 
8830  auto FS = std::make_unique<FunctionSummary>(
8831  GVFlags, InstCount, FFlags, /*EntryCount=*/0, std::move(Refs),
8832  std::move(Calls), std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTests),
8833  std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeVCalls),
8834  std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadVCalls),
8835  std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeConstVCalls),
8836  std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls),
8837  std::move(ParamAccesses), std::move(Callsites), std::move(Allocs));
8838 
8839  FS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
8840 
8841  addGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
8842  ID, std::move(FS));
8843 
8844  return false;
8845 }
8846 
8847 /// VariableSummary
8848 /// ::= 'variable' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags
8849 /// [',' OptionalRefs]? ')'
8850 bool LLParser::parseVariableSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
8851  unsigned ID) {
8852  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_variable);
8853  Lex.Lex();
8854 
8855  StringRef ModulePath;
8856  GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
8857  GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility,
8858  /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
8859  /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
8860  GlobalVarSummary::GVarFlags GVarFlags(/*ReadOnly*/ false,
8861  /* WriteOnly */ false,
8862  /* Constant */ false,
8863  GlobalObject::VCallVisibilityPublic);
8864  std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs;
8865  VTableFuncList VTableFuncs;
8866  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8867  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8868  parseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
8869  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || parseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
8870  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8871  parseGVarFlags(GVarFlags))
8872  return true;
8873 
8874  // parse optional fields
8875  while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8876  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8877  case lltok::kw_vTableFuncs:
8878  if (parseOptionalVTableFuncs(VTableFuncs))
8879  return true;
8880  break;
8881  case lltok::kw_refs:
8882  if (parseOptionalRefs(Refs))
8883  return true;
8884  break;
8885  default:
8886  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected optional variable summary field");
8887  }
8888  }
8889 
8890  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8891  return true;
8892 
8893  auto GS =
8894  std::make_unique<GlobalVarSummary>(GVFlags, GVarFlags, std::move(Refs));
8895 
8896  GS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
8897  GS->setVTableFuncs(std::move(VTableFuncs));
8898 
8899  addGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
8900  ID, std::move(GS));
8901 
8902  return false;
8903 }

8905 /// AliasSummary
8906 /// ::= 'alias' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags ','
8907 /// 'aliasee' ':' GVReference ')'
8908 bool LLParser::parseAliasSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
8909  unsigned ID) {
8910  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_alias);
8911  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8912  Lex.Lex();
8913 
8914  StringRef ModulePath;
8915  GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
8916  GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility,
8917  /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
8918  /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
8919  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8920  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8921  parseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
8922  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || parseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
8923  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8924  parseToken(lltok::kw_aliasee, "expected 'aliasee' here") ||
8925  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
8926  return true;
8927 
8928  ValueInfo AliaseeVI;
8929  unsigned GVId;
8930  if (parseGVReference(AliaseeVI, GVId))
8931  return true;
8932 
8933  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8934  return true;
8935 
8936  auto AS = std::make_unique<AliasSummary>(GVFlags);
8937 
8938  AS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
8939 
8940  // Record forward reference if the aliasee is not parsed yet.
8941  if (AliaseeVI.getRef() == FwdVIRef) {
8942  ForwardRefAliasees[GVId].emplace_back(AS.get(), Loc);
8943  } else {
8944  auto Summary = Index->findSummaryInModule(AliaseeVI, ModulePath);
8945  assert(Summary && "Aliasee must be a definition");
8946  AS->setAliasee(AliaseeVI, Summary);
8947  }
8948 
8949  addGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
8950  ID, std::move(AS));
8951 
8952  return false;
8953 }

8955 /// Flag

8959  return tokError("expected integer");
8960  Val = (unsigned)Lex.getAPSIntVal().getBoolValue();
8961  Lex.Lex();
8962  return false;

8965 /// OptionalFFlags
8966 /// := 'funcFlags' ':' '(' ['readNone' ':' Flag]?
8967 /// [',' 'readOnly' ':' Flag]? [',' 'noRecurse' ':' Flag]?
8968 /// [',' 'returnDoesNotAlias' ':' Flag]? ')'
8969 /// [',' 'noInline' ':' Flag]? ')'
8970 /// [',' 'alwaysInline' ':' Flag]? ')'
8971 /// [',' 'noUnwind' ':' Flag]? ')'
8972 /// [',' 'mayThrow' ':' Flag]? ')'
8973 /// [',' 'hasUnknownCall' ':' Flag]? ')'
8974 /// [',' 'mustBeUnreachable' ':' Flag]? ')'
8975 
8976 bool LLParser::parseOptionalFFlags(FunctionSummary::FFlags &FFlags) {
8977  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_funcFlags);
8978  Lex.Lex();
8979 
8980  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in funcFlags") ||
8981  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in funcFlags"))
8982  return true;
8983 
8984  do {
8985  unsigned Val = 0;
8986  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8987  case lltok::kw_readNone:
8988  Lex.Lex();
8989  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
8990  return true;
8991  FFlags.ReadNone = Val;
8992  break;
8993  case lltok::kw_readOnly:
8994  Lex.Lex();
8995  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
8996  return true;
8997  FFlags.ReadOnly = Val;
8998  break;
8999  case lltok::kw_noRecurse:
9000  Lex.Lex();
9001  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9002  return true;
9003  FFlags.NoRecurse = Val;
9004  break;
9005  case lltok::kw_returnDoesNotAlias:
9006  Lex.Lex();
9007  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9008  return true;
9009  FFlags.ReturnDoesNotAlias = Val;
9010  break;
9011  case lltok::kw_noInline:
9012  Lex.Lex();
9013  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9014  return true;
9015  FFlags.NoInline = Val;
9016  break;
9017  case lltok::kw_alwaysInline:
9018  Lex.Lex();
9019  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9020  return true;
9021  FFlags.AlwaysInline = Val;
9022  break;
9023  case lltok::kw_noUnwind:
9024  Lex.Lex();
9025  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9026  return true;
9027  FFlags.NoUnwind = Val;
9028  break;
9029  case lltok::kw_mayThrow:
9030  Lex.Lex();
9031  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9032  return true;
9033  FFlags.MayThrow = Val;
9034  break;
9035  case lltok::kw_hasUnknownCall:
9036  Lex.Lex();
9037  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9038  return true;
9039  FFlags.HasUnknownCall = Val;
9040  break;
9041  case lltok::kw_mustBeUnreachable:
9042  Lex.Lex();
9043  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseFlag(Val))
9044  return true;
9045  FFlags.MustBeUnreachable = Val;
9046  break;
9047  default:
9048  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected function flag type");
9049  }
9050  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9051 
9052  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in funcFlags"))
9053  return true;
9054 
9055  return false;
9056 }

9058 /// OptionalCalls
9059 /// := 'calls' ':' '(' Call [',' Call]* ')'
9060 /// Call ::= '(' 'callee' ':' GVReference
9061 /// [( ',' 'hotness' ':' Hotness | ',' 'relbf' ':' UInt32 )]? ')'
9062 bool LLParser::parseOptionalCalls(std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> &Calls) {
9063  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_calls);
9064  Lex.Lex();
9065 
9066  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in calls") ||
9067  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in calls"))
9068  return true;
9069 
9070  IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
9071  // parse each call edge
9072  do {
9073  ValueInfo VI;
9074  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in call") ||
9075  parseToken(lltok::kw_callee, "expected 'callee' in call") ||
9076  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'"))
9077  return true;
9078 
9079  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
9080  unsigned GVId;
9081  if (parseGVReference(VI, GVId))
9082  return true;
9083 
9084  CalleeInfo::HotnessType Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Unknown;
9085  unsigned RelBF = 0;
9086  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
9087  // Expect either hotness or relbf
9088  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_hotness)) {
9089  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseHotness(Hotness))
9090  return true;
9091  } else {
9092  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_relbf, "expected relbf") ||
9093  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseUInt32(RelBF))
9094  return true;
9095  }
9096  }
9097  // Keep track of the Call array index needing a forward reference.
9098  // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
9099  // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
9100  if (VI.getRef() == FwdVIRef)
9101  IdToIndexMap[GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(Calls.size(), Loc));
9102  Calls.push_back(FunctionSummary::EdgeTy{VI, CalleeInfo(Hotness, RelBF)});
9103 
9104  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in call"))
9105  return true;
9106  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9107 
9108  // Now that the Calls vector is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
9109  // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
9110  for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
9111  auto &Infos = ForwardRefValueInfos[I.first];
9112  for (auto P : I.second) {
9113  assert(Calls[P.first].first.getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
9114  "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
9115  Infos.emplace_back(&Calls[P.first].first, P.second);
9116  }
9117  }
9118 
9119  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in calls"))
9120  return true;
9121 
9122  return false;
9123 }

9125 /// Hotness
9126 /// := ('unknown'|'cold'|'none'|'hot'|'critical')
9127 bool LLParser::parseHotness(CalleeInfo::HotnessType &Hotness) {
9128  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
9129  case lltok::kw_unknown:
9130  Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Unknown;
9131  break;
9132  case lltok::kw_cold:
9133  Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Cold;
9134  break;
9135  case lltok::kw_none:
9136  Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::None;
9137  break;
9138  case lltok::kw_hot:
9139  Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Hot;
9140  break;
9141  case lltok::kw_critical:
9142  Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Critical;
9143  break;
9144  default:
9145  return error(Lex.getLoc(), "invalid call edge hotness");
9146  }
9147  Lex.Lex();
9148  return false;
9149 }

9151 /// OptionalVTableFuncs
9152 /// := 'vTableFuncs' ':' '(' VTableFunc [',' VTableFunc]* ')'
9153 /// VTableFunc ::= '(' 'virtFunc' ':' GVReference ',' 'offset' ':' UInt64 ')'
9154 bool LLParser::parseOptionalVTableFuncs(VTableFuncList &VTableFuncs) {
9155  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_vTableFuncs);
9156  Lex.Lex();
9157 
9158  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in vTableFuncs") ||
9159  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in vTableFuncs"))
9160  return true;
9161 
9162  IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
9163  // parse each virtual function pair
9164  do {
9165  ValueInfo VI;
9166  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in vTableFunc") ||
9167  parseToken(lltok::kw_virtFunc, "expected 'callee' in vTableFunc") ||
9168  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'"))
9169  return true;
9170 
9171  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
9172  unsigned GVId;
9173  if (parseGVReference(VI, GVId))
9174  return true;
9175 
9176  uint64_t Offset;
9177  if (parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma") ||
9178  parseToken(lltok::kw_offset, "expected offset") ||
9179  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || parseUInt64(Offset))
9180  return true;
9181 
9182  // Keep track of the VTableFuncs array index needing a forward reference.
9183  // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
9184  // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
9185  if (VI == EmptyVI)
9186  IdToIndexMap[GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(VTableFuncs.size(), Loc));
9187  VTableFuncs.push_back({VI, Offset});
9188 
9189  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in vTableFunc"))
9190  return true;
9191  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9192 
9193  // Now that the VTableFuncs vector is finalized, it is safe to save the
9194  // locations of any forward GV references that need updating later.
9195  for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
9196  auto &Infos = ForwardRefValueInfos[I.first];
9197  for (auto P : I.second) {
9198  assert(VTableFuncs[P.first].FuncVI == EmptyVI &&
9199  "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
9200  Infos.emplace_back(&VTableFuncs[P.first].FuncVI, P.second);
9201  }
9202  }
9203 
9204  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in vTableFuncs"))
9205  return true;
9206 
9207  return false;
9208 }

9213  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || parseUInt64(ParamNo))
9214  return true;

9218 /// ParamAccessOffset := 'offset' ':' '[' APSINTVAL ',' APSINTVAL ']'
9219 bool LLParser::parseParamAccessOffset(ConstantRange &Range) {
9220  APSInt Lower;
9221  APSInt Upper;
9222  auto ParseAPSInt = [&](APSInt &Val) {
9223  if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt)
9224  return tokError("expected integer");
9225  Val = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
9226  Val = Val.extOrTrunc(FunctionSummary::ParamAccess::RangeWidth);
9227  Val.setIsSigned(true);
9228  Lex.Lex();
9229  return false;
9230  };
9231  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_offset, "expected 'offset' here") ||
9232  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
9233  parseToken(lltok::lsquare, "expected '[' here") || ParseAPSInt(Lower) ||
9234  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || ParseAPSInt(Upper) ||
9235  parseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected ']' here"))
9236  return true;
9237 
9238  ++Upper;
9239  Range =
9240  (Lower == Upper && !Lower.isMaxValue())
9241  ? ConstantRange::getEmpty(FunctionSummary::ParamAccess::RangeWidth)
9242  : ConstantRange(Lower, Upper);
9243 
9244  return false;
9245 }

9247 /// ParamAccessCall
9248 /// := '(' 'callee' ':' GVReference ',' ParamNo ',' ParamAccessOffset ')'
9249 bool LLParser::parseParamAccessCall(FunctionSummary::ParamAccess::Call &Call,
9250  IdLocListType &IdLocList) {
9251  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
9252  parseToken(lltok::kw_callee, "expected 'callee' here") ||
9253  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
9254  return true;
9255 
9256  unsigned GVId;
9257  ValueInfo VI;
9258  LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
9259  if (parseGVReference(VI, GVId))
9260  return true;

9262  Call.Callee = VI;
9263  IdLocList.emplace_back(GVId, Loc);
9264 
9265  if (parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
9266  parseParamNo(Call.ParamNo) ||
9267  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
9268  parseParamAccessOffset(Call.Offsets))
9269  return true;
9270 
9271  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
9272  return true;
9273 
9274  return false;
9275 }

9277 /// ParamAccess
9278 /// := '(' ParamNo ',' ParamAccessOffset [',' OptionalParamAccessCalls]? ')'
9279 /// OptionalParamAccessCalls := '(' Call [',' Call]* ')'
9280 bool LLParser::parseParamAccess(FunctionSummary::ParamAccess &Param,
9281  IdLocListType &IdLocList) {
9282  if (parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
9283  parseParamNo(Param.ParamNo) ||
9284  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
9285  parseParamAccessOffset(Param.Use))
9286  return true;
9287 
9288  if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
9289  if (parseToken(lltok::kw_calls, "expected 'calls' here") ||
9290  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
9291  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
9292  return true;

9294  FunctionSummary::ParamAccess::Call Call;
9295  if (parseParamAccessCall(Call, IdLocList))
9296  return true;
9297  Param.Calls.push_back(Call);
9298  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9299 
9300  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
9301  return true;
9302  }
9303 
9304  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
9305  return true;
9306 
9307  return false;
9308 }

9310 /// OptionalParamAccesses
9311 /// := 'params' ':' '(' ParamAccess [',' ParamAccess]* ')'
9312 bool LLParser::parseOptionalParamAccesses(
9313  std::vector<FunctionSummary::ParamAccess> &Params) {
9314  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_params);
9315  Lex.Lex();
9316 
9317  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
9318  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
9319  return true;
9320 
9321  IdLocListType VContexts;
9322  size_t CallsNum = 0;
9323  do {
9324  FunctionSummary::ParamAccess ParamAccess;
9325  if (parseParamAccess(ParamAccess, VContexts))
9326  return true;
9327  CallsNum += ParamAccess.Calls.size();
9328  assert(VContexts.size() == CallsNum);
9329  (void)CallsNum;
9330  Params.emplace_back(std::move(ParamAccess));
9331  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9332 
9333  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
9334  return true;
9335 
9336  // Now that the Params is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
9337  // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
9338  IdLocListType::const_iterator ItContext = VContexts.begin();
9339  for (auto &PA : Params) {
9340  for (auto &C : PA.Calls) {
9341  if (C.Callee.getRef() == FwdVIRef)
9342  ForwardRefValueInfos[ItContext->first].emplace_back(&C.Callee,
9343  ItContext->second);
9344  ++ItContext;
9345  }
9346  }
9347  assert(ItContext == VContexts.end());
9348 
9349  return false;
9350 }

9352 /// OptionalRefs
9353 /// := 'refs' ':' '(' GVReference [',' GVReference]* ')'
9354 bool LLParser::parseOptionalRefs(std::vector<ValueInfo> &Refs) {
9355  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_refs);
9356  Lex.Lex();
9357 
9358  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in refs") ||
9359  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in refs"))
9360  return true;
9361 
9362  struct ValueContext {
9363  ValueInfo VI;
9364  unsigned GVId;
9365  LocTy Loc;
9366  };
9367  std::vector<ValueContext> VContexts;
9368  // parse each ref edge
9369  do {
9370  ValueContext VC;
9371  VC.Loc = Lex.getLoc();
9372  if (parseGVReference(VC.VI, VC.GVId))
9373  return true;
9374  VContexts.push_back(VC);
9375  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
9376 
9377  // Sort value contexts so that ones with writeonly
9378  // and readonly ValueInfo are at the end of VContexts vector.
9379  // See FunctionSummary::specialRefCounts()
9380  llvm::sort(VContexts, [](const ValueContext &VC1, const ValueContext &VC2) {
9381  return VC1.VI.getAccessSpecifier() < VC2.VI.getAccessSpecifier();
9382  });
9383 
9384  IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
9385  for (auto &VC : VContexts) {
9386  // Keep track of the Refs array index needing a forward reference.
9387  // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
9388  // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
9389  if (VC.VI.getRef() == FwdVIRef)
9390  IdToIndexMap[VC.GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(Refs.size(), VC.Loc));
9391  Refs.push_back(VC.VI);
9392  }
9393 
9394  // Now that the Refs vector is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
9395  // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
9396  for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
9397  auto &Infos = ForwardRefValueInfos[I.first];
9398  for (auto P : I.second) {
9399  assert(Refs[P.first].getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
9400  "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
9401  Infos.emplace_back(&Refs[P.first], P.second);
9402  }
9403  }
9404 
9405  if (parseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in refs"))
9406  return true;
9407 
9408  return false;
9409 }
9410 
9411 /// OptionalTypeIdInfo
9412 /// := 'typeidinfo' ':' '(' [',' TypeTests]? [',' TypeTestAssumeVCalls]?
9413 /// [',' TypeCheckedLoadVCalls]? [',' TypeTestAssumeConstVCalls]?
9414 /// [',' TypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls]? ')'
9415 bool LLParser::parseOptionalTypeIdInfo(
9416  FunctionSummary::TypeIdInfo &TypeIdInfo) {
9417  assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeIdInfo);
9418  Lex.Lex();
9419 
9420  if (parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
9421  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in typeIdInfo"))
9422  return true;
9423 
9424  do {
9425  switch (Lex.getKind()) {
9426  case lltok::kw_typeTests:
9427  if (parseTypeTests(TypeIdInfo.TypeTests))
9428  return true;
9429  break;

9923 bool LLParser::parseOptionalCallsites(std::vector<CallsiteInfo> &Callsites) {

9925  Lex.Lex();

9928  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in callsites"))

9936  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'"))
9937  return true;

9955  unsigned V = 0;

9962  parseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' in callsite") ||
9963  parseToken(lltok::kw_stackIds, "expected 'stackIds' in callsite") ||
9964  parseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") ||
9965  parseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in stackIds"))

9972  return true;
9973  StackIdIndices.push_back(Index->addOrGetStackIdIndex(StackId));
9974  } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));

9980  // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
9981  // can only do so once the SmallVector is finalized.

Definition: LLToken.h:412
type
AMD64 Optimization Manual has some nice information about optimizing integer multiplication by a constant How much of it applies to Intel s X86 implementation There are definite trade offs to xmm0 cvttss2siq rdx jb L3 subss xmm0 rax cvttss2siq rdx xorq rdx rax ret instead of xmm1 cvttss2siq rcx movaps xmm2 subss xmm2 cvttss2siq rax rdx xorq rax ucomiss xmm0 cmovb rax ret Seems like the jb branch has high likelihood of being taken It would have saved a few instructions It s not possible to reference and DH registers in an instruction requiring REX prefix divb and mulb both produce results in AH If isel emits a CopyFromReg which gets turned into a movb and that can be allocated a r8b r15b To get around isel emits a CopyFromReg from AX and then right shift it down by and truncate it It s not pretty but it works We need some register allocation magic to make the hack go which would often require a callee saved register Callees usually need to keep this value live for most of their body so it doesn t add a significant burden on them We currently implement this in however this is suboptimal because it means that it would be quite awkward to implement the optimization for callers A better implementation would be to relax the LLVM IR rules for sret arguments to allow a function with an sret argument to have a non void return type
